title: cheese krispies
directions: Blend cheese into softened oleo.
Work in flour.
Add Rice Krispies.
Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes. Yield:
10 to 12 dozen.

title: salad bar swedish meatballs
directions: Combine beef and seasonings and egg; make into golf ball size balls.
Let sit in fridge for 1 hour.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and gradually beat in sugar.
Add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth. Add dry ingredients and fold in berries.
Spread batter into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with crumb mixture.

title: mint chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Fold in sugar, salt and mint chips.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Turn off oven.
Leave in oven overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars.
Cream until light and creamy.
Add unbeaten egg and beat well.
Add flour which has been sifted with soda.
Add vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Roll 1/2 teaspoon in hand to form a small ball. Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: papier-mache paste
directions: In a heavy saucepan, stir flour into cold water.
Ask a grownup to cook over low heat until the mixture thickens to a creamy paste. Cool, then add a few drops of peppermint oil.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Beat egg and water together in a bowl.
Mix crumbs and seasonings together in another bowl.
Pull skin off chicken, if desired.
Put a piece of chicken in egg and then in bread crumb mixture.
Put chicken on baking pan, ungreased, in oven at 350° for 1 hour (less for small pieces of chicken).

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix by hand the first 3 ingredients.
Mix together egg, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix shortening and sugar well. Add molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well. Pinch a small piece of cookie mixture.
Roll into a small ball. Dip into sugar.
Put on cookie sheet and press down with bottom of small glass that has been greased and sugared.
Do not grease pan. Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Soften butter at room temperature and mix into biscuit mix with hands, making a crumbly mixture.
Mash peaches and juice in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour flour mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese-sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring cheese to room temperature.
Mix cheese and sausage with biscuit mix using fork.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil; boil 1 minute. Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased waxed paper.
Cool thoroughly.

title: chocolate sour cream black walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, soda and cocoa together.
Add this to creamed mixture, alternately with sour cream and milk. Beat well.
Flour nuts with 2 tablespoons flour and fold into cake mixture.
Add vanilla and beat again.
Bake in slow oven for approximately 2 hours or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine and bring to a hard boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from the stove and add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir then drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: chicken no peek
directions: Mix in bowl.
Then put in a well-greased bowl or in pan.
Add chicken, then pour remaining onion soup over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and do not peek while cooking.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serves 6 people.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Brown beef, onion and bell pepper together.
Drain excess grease.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit, reserving 1 to 1 1/2 cups of juice.
Mix juice with 1 small package of instant vanilla pudding and 2 tablespoons of Tang.
Pour over fruit.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: salted nut squares
directions: Place 1/2 peanuts in an ungreased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: cheese petit fours
directions: Beat together all ingredients.
Cut crust from bread slices. Spread each layer with mixture and quarter.
Spread sides of quarters.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10-15 minutes.
Can be frozen until ready to bake.

title: holiday potatoes
directions: Shred potatoes into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream. Pour over potatoes and cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Sprinkle with corn flakes and drizzle with 3 tablespoons butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with pimento strips and parsley. Serves 12.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Poke holes in top of cake as soon as it is removed from oven.
Pour ice cream topping over cake.
When cooled, frost with whipped topping; sprinkle with candy pieces.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Quickly put in remaining ingredients.

title: mexican vegetable soup
directions: Combine soup, chilies and chili powder.
Bring to boil and then simmer 3 minutes.
Garnish with avocado.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix in blender.
To serve, mix 2 or 3 tablespoons of mix and 1 cup of hot water.

title: family affair
directions: Mix and bake cake in 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Mix Jell-O as directed; let set slightly.
Stir in strawberries and gel completely.
Mix pudding per directions on box with milk.
Use medium size punch bowl.
Layer Jell-O, cake (cut in pieces), layer pudding and Cool Whip.
Keep layering until bowl is full.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Slice onions over chops

title: mushroom stuffed fish
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients except fish. Mix.
Place fish in a single layer in well-greased baking dish. Cover fish evenly with stuffing mix.
Place in 400° oven for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Serves 6.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Boil molasses, sugar and vinegar to hard boil stage (265 - 270 degrees). Remove from fire add butter, baking soda and salt. Stir only enough to blend. Pour into a well buttered pan. When cool pull until light and porous. Then cut in 1 1/2 inch pieces.

title: smothered cabbage
directions: In a heavy pot, saute ham until slightly brown.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add cabbage and sweet pepper and cook down until soft and juicy.
Uncover and cook until liquid evaporates. Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Serves 6.

title: roasted italian potato fans
directions: You may peel potatoes or leave skins on and wash well.
Slice each potato crosswise into 1/4-inch slices, being careful to cut each slice only 3/4 of the way through the potato.
Place potatoes in a baking dish and brush with melted butter.
Place 1 onion ring between each potato slice.
Pour Italian dressing over potatoes and sprinkle with salt, basil and Parmesan cheese.
Cook at 400° for about 1 hour until potatoes are tender.
Brush potatoes during cooking with dressing from bottom of pan.
For lighter dish, skip butter and use nonfat dressing.
This recipe works well in the microwave.

title: hop cough syrup *
directions: Boil water, hops and chestnut leaves down to 1 1/2 cups.
Add brown sugar.
Boil to syrup.

title: ribbon mold
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine with cold water; set aside.
Bring milk to boil.
Add sugar and blend until smooth.
Add gelatin and stir. Add sour cream and vanilla; blend until smooth.

title: italian ice
directions: Boil sugar and water 5 minutes.
Add fruit juices and rind. Cool, strain and freeze.
Yield:
Approximately 2 quarts.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in butter, cornmeal and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beaten egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mix gently, but thoroughly.

title: texas rattlesnake chilimidland, texas
directions: In a 5 qt. saucepan, heat the oil and cook the onion, green pepper and garlic until tender. Add the meat and cool until done (about 5 minutes).
Stir in seasonings, tomatoes and tomato paste. Heat to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours. Before serving, add water and return chili to boiling.
Stir in uncooked pasta.
Continue boiling, stirring frequently about 10 to 15 minutes, until pasta is tender.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: oniony potato grill
directions: On 4 sheets of heavy-duty aluminum foil (each about 10 x 18-inches), equally divide potatoes.
Top each with 2 tablespoons Lipton Onion Butter and sprinkle with parsley.
Wrap foil loosely, sealing edges airtight with double fold.
Grill 30 minutes or until tender.

title: tofu burgers
directions: Slice tofu in 1/2-inch slices.
Pour olive oil into nonstick frypan and heat on low.
Once oil is hot, add jalapeno and garlic; cook until soft.
Add tofu slices and cook on low heat until brown on both sides.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Serve on Kaiser roll topped with bean sprouts and mustard.

title: wacky chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add oil, vinegar and cold water.
Mix with mixer, until smooth.
Pour into cake pan. Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and nutmeg.
Add ice cream, egg nog, cream and milk.
Stir and stir and stir and stir and stir.
Pour in booze.
Beat egg whites and mix together.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes plenty.

title: 5 minute boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar and dry pudding.
Add milk slowly.
Mix well and beat with an electric mixer for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate.
Stir well each time before serving.
If too thick, add milk to thin. Serve with dollops of Cool Whip and dash of ginger.

title: joe's barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer until onions and celery are soft.

title: toasted spice cake with the frosting baked in
directions: Blend Crisco with sugar and egg yolks.
Dissolve soda in milk. Add milk mixture alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Spread batter into greased and floured cake pan.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine pudding, sugars and
milk
in
saucepan.
Blend well. Cook and stir over low
heat
until sugar is completely dissolved. Continue cooking,	without stirring, until mixture comes to a full boil.	Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Remove the casing from the sausage and brown in a heavy pan on top of stove.
Drain off excess fat.
Add chopped celery and cook for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add all remaining ingredients except green peppers.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add green pepper; cover and simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Serve with garlic butter Italian bread and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: butterscotch chewies
directions: Melt oleo over low heat in a pan.
Add brown sugar and stir until all lumps dissolve.
Remove from heat and add 2 eggs, beating until well blended.
Mix flour with pecans.
Stir into first mixture and add vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Turn batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2 pan and bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.
Do not over bake.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to flour and mix well.
Add buttermilk.
Turn out on board; knead until smooth.
May need to use more flour to handle it.
When kneaded, roll out 1/4-inch thick; cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter; place in greased pan after folding over in half.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Start with lettuce and layer in a large casserole dish or bowl.
After the lettuce, layer the celery, onion, green pepper, peas and mayonnaise.
Sprinkle the sugar over that and cover with the cheese.
Fry the bacon and crumble it over the top.
Cover the bowl tightly and let it set in the refrigerator for a few hours before serving for the best flavor.

title: laxative bars
directions: Grind ingredients 2 or 3 times until well mixed.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Eat as needed.
Store airtight in refrigerator.

title: beer cheese (dip)
directions: Mix together
cheese,
garlic, Worcestershire sauce and mustard with enough beer to make it spreadable.
Chill.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and place in 13 x 9-inch dish.
Beat eggs, sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour mixture over bread. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: outrageous garlic bread
directions: Combine butter and garlic, let set for a couple of hours. Spread bread with garlic butter mixture, shred cheese and combine with mayonnaise.
Spread on bread, broil until golden and cheese is melted.
This goes great with anything.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut in flour and shortening.
Mix in remaining ingredients with a fork.
Makes 2 crust pie.

title: mexican creams(candy)
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add other ingredients and cook on medium heat to 232° on candy thermometer, stirring constantly (234° if damp weather).
Then cool until you can touch bottom of pan.
Beat until it holds a peak, then drop by spoon onto waxed paper to form individual candies.
Or pour into a Saran lined pan and cut into squares.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple with dry instant pudding.
Add Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix and chill.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with pretzels or veggies.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Butter the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pat half the mixture over the graham crackers, then place a second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour the remaining mixture on and cover with more crackers.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In
small
mixing
bowl beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and
cream.
Stir
in vanilla, brandy and pecans.
Pour into unbaked
pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set.

title: grilled cheese pie
directions: Combine eggs, flour, salt, pepper, oregano, Parmesan and 1/2 cup of the milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 the Swiss cheese.
Pour into a buttered 9-inch quiche or pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle on the rest of the Swiss cheese and bake about 2 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.

title: buttermilk nut candy(like pralines)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, soda and buttermilk in a heavy iron skillet. Cook over medium heat. Bring to a rolling boil, stirring often to prevent burning or boiling over. Remove from heat. Add butter, flavoring and nuts. Beat until creamy and thick. Drop on waxed paper lined pan.

title: sloppy joe bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Generously grease a square pan.
Prepare meat and Sloppy Joe sauce as directed on can.

title: very moist corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Add nuts, bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

title: imperial crab
directions: Mix ingredients and add crabmeat.
Place in a baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs (little), cover with melted oleo and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Sprinkle
nuts	on
top of mix.
Blend cheese, eggs and sugar. Pour
over
top and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 1 hour before cutting.

title: hershey's fudge cake
directions: Sift dry
ingredients.	Cream
shortening, adding sugar gradually.	Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture alternately
with buttermilk.
Mix cocoa and hot water to form a
paste.
Add to batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and blend well. Serve with apple wedges, pear wedges or gingersnaps. May be served out of a cleaned out pumpkin. Yield: 1 1/2 quarts.

title: appetizer ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ham, pork, bread crumbs, milk, onions, mustard and egg; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in bottom of casserole.
Mix other ingredients and pour over potatoes.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Melt margarine; add spices.
Place sugar in bowl and add margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat, with a mixer, for 30 minutes on medium speed.
Seal in jar.
Keep in fridge.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Melt stick of butter in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer remaining ingredients on top of butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crunchy turkey casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green peppers in butter or margarine. Mix sauteed vegetables with turkey, water chestnuts, mushrooms and undiluted soup.
Line a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with one can of the chow mein noodles; pour turkey mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle remaining can of chow mein noodles over top of turkey mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: lita's green bean casserole
directions: Mix the drained corn and green beans with the remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: three step chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, except cornstarch.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Skim off excess grease.
Remove bay leaves and add enough water to cornstarch to make paste that will pour.
Add to chili.
Allow to thicken.

title: boston salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and mix it with whipped Dream Whip.
Add to the cooled jello mixture.
Add pineapple and juice.
Add nuts.
Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Pretty at Christmas.

title: fluffy orange dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Save 1/4 cup crumbs.
Chill.
Combine Jell-O with water, sugar and orange juice.
Heat until Jell-O and sugar dissolve.
Chill until partially set.
Chill evaporated milk thoroughly.
Whip and fold into partially set Jell-O with orange peel.
Pile over crumb crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Melt butter in top of double boiler over simmering water; add oats and milk, stirring well.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly; stir in egg.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in a small mixing bowl; add to oatmeal mixture, stirring well.
Stir in raisins, pecans and vanilla.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool slightly on cookie sheets.
Remove to wire racks to cool. Yields approximately 3 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into hot, well-greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 18 muffins.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls. Add meatballs to 2 bottles of your favorite barbecue sauce and slow cook in crock-pot for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 loaf pans.
In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar, walnuts, baking powder and salt.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water. Simmer 25 minutes.
Meanwhile in medium mixing bowl, combine 1 cup flour, yeast, sugar, onion and salt; mix well.
Add warm water and oil.
Mix by hand until almost smooth.
Stir in corn chips and enough remaining flour to make a stiff batter. Spread in well-greased 10-inch pie pan, forming a rim around edge.
Cover; let rise in a warm place about 20 minutes.
Spread meat filling over dough. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until edge is light golden brown and crisp.
Sprinkle cheese, lettuce and tomatoes on top.
Serve immediately.

title: our famous popovers
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon-colored.
Add warm milk; stir well.
Add flour and salt, stirring just until blended.

title: donna's salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix in small amounts of vinegar, mayonnaise and sugar.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: carrot honey
directions: Mix ingredients.
Simmer until thick.
Place in containers and freeze.
Serve with hot or cold meat.

title: cinnamon chip muffins
directions: Mix the following dry ingredients together:
flour, sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add butter, eggs, milk and vanilla to the dry ingredients; mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.

title: shrimp orleans
directions: Melt butter and olive oil.
Add other ingredients.
Saute 5 to 6 minutes.
Serve over fettucini noodles.

title: orange mint coffee
directions: Place 1 sprig of mint and 1 orange slice in each of 6 cups. Pour fresh brewed coffee into each cup.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: popcorn ball cups
directions: You will need paper cups.

title: frozen pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Remove pizza from carton and wrapper. Place pizza on oven rack.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until the crust is golden brown.

title: sugar-free banana pie
directions: Make pie mix as directed.
Mix in banana and drained pineapple.
Mix in 3 tablespoons of Cool Whip.
Pour mixture in cooled pie shell.
Top with rest of Cool Whip.
Chill in fridge for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix other ingredients and add to jello.
Congeal and serve on lettuce leaf with mayonnaise. Chopped maraschino cherries may be added for color if desired.

title: carrots in cream
directions: Heat cream and egg yolks, butter, sugar and nutmeg.
Cook slowly until thickened, stirring constantly.
Fold into hot carrot slices and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter, add onions and cook until golden brown.
Add water and bouillon.
Mix; bring to boil and reduce heat.
Cook gently for 30 minutes.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and press into a ball; then chill.

title: roasted mustard potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a roasting pan three times to coat with the vegetable oil.
Put the mustard, paprika, cumin, chili powder and cayenne pepper in a large bowl.
Whisk to blend.
Prick the potatoes several times with the tines of a fork and add them to the bowl.
Toss to coat the potatoes evenly.
Pour the coated potatoes into prepared roasting pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings, 137 calories, 1.7 fat.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch chips and peanut butter in an 8-cup glass measure.
Microwave at 70% power for about 5 minutes.
Stir until melted.
Fold in marshmallows and peanuts. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until set.
Cut into squares.

title: gingered chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in mayonnaise mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill and serve with a loaf of sliced sourdough bread.

title: dirt cake
directions: Line flower pots completely with foil; set aside.
Crush cookies until they resemble potting soil.
Place 1 cup crumbs (or more) in each flower pot; set aside.
Cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla together until blended; set aside.
Combine pudding mix and milk, fold in whipped topping.
Gently fold cheese and pudding mixtures together.
Pour half the mixture into each flower pot. Top with remaining cookie crumbs.
Cover with foil; refrigerate. When ready to serve, remove foil; top with silk or plastic flowers whose stems have been wrapped in foil.
Display with plastic gardening tools if desired.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and white sugar; beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend into peanut butter mixture.
Spread into a 13 x 9-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips over surface.
Place in a 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and run knife through to swirl.
Return to oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: brownie cheese cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

In large mixing bowl, blend cake mix, coconut, butter and 1 egg on low speed until mixture is crumbly. Press very lightly in ungreased baking pan (13 x 8 x 2-inch). Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons vanilla until smooth and fluffy.
Spread over cake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon vanilla until smooth.
Spread over cooled cheese cake.
Refrigerate at least 8 hours before serving.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Add chopped dried beef and other ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze it to drain out water.
Mix with other ingredients and serve with tostada "Scoops" or other firm crackers for dipping.

title: beef barbecue brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt. Place in roasting pan lined with heavy-duty foil. Mix all other ingredients; pour over beef.
Wrap foil tightly around it. Cook at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Prepare fruit and nuts.
Crush crackers.
Melt marshmallows in 1 cup milk over low heat.
Mix ingredients in large bowl (may need to use your hands).
Pack in desired pans lined with foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and onion.
Stir to separate meat. Pour off fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: so easy sweet pickles
directions: Pour off all juice from a quart jar of dill pickles.
Do not wash.
Slice pickles thin.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Sit for 3 days; turn every time you are passing icebox for first day or two.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs first.
Add the next 4 ingredients.
Stir in coconut last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: fried rabbit
directions: Cut up the rabbit and pressure cook it for about 15 minutes. Drain.
Dip each piece into the egg and then into the salt and peppered flour.
Brown the rabbit in a skillet with shortening over medium heat.
Slice the onion up and put around the rabbit. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crumble 1/2 package crackers in bottom of casserole dish. Dice 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 cup cheese on top of crackers.
Cook broccoli; drain and mix with 1/2 cup milk and can of soup.
Pour into casserole on top of cheese.
Put remaining cheese on top of broccoli.
Crumble 1/2 package crackers on cheese; put 1/2 stick butter on top.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add Cheez Whiz; stir until mixed. Add other ingredients. Place broccoli and rice in dish. Pour over broccoli and rice. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one (1) hour.

title: egg and olive spread
directions: Mix all ingredients, spread on bread.

title: cheese snaps(makes about 36)
directions: Blend cheese and butter together; work in flour, cayenne and salt.
Place dough in waxed paper and press gently together.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Stuff each date with a piece of walnut and place in center of square.
Press dough tightly around date in palm of hand.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a hot oven, 400°, for about 12 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned. Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serve with a salad or as a cookie.

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add flour.
Work it in with your hands.
Divide into 2 or 4 parts and pat out 1/2-inch thick on ungreased cookie sheet.
Roll top smooth with a rolling pin. Prick generously with fork.
Put into cold oven.
Set temperature at 325°.
Bake 35 to 50 minutes (depending on oven) until light golden color.
Cut into wedges while hot.
Store in tightly covered tin.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Beat the first 6 ingredients well.
Add 1/2 cup flour which has been added to baking powder and mix well.
Fold in egg whites.
Put in 3 tablespoons of the syrup in the cake batter.
Bake in layers on flat pan at 350° until done.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: In enough broth to cover, boil onion, bell pepper and celery for 10 minutes.
Pour into large bowl, add corn bread and white bread.
Add seasonings and stir eggs into bread mixture.
Add enough broth to make batter runny.
Bake in greased dish at 400° for 1 hour.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Combine the first 3 items and refrigerate.
Then layer bananas, vanilla wafers, pudding mixture, and repeat.
Can substitute crushed pineapple or be an addition to the recipe.

title: pasta in wiener rafts
directions: Prepare Pasta Accents as directed on package until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in mustard.
Keep warm.
Meanwhile, make 4 slashes, 1 inch apart, on 1 side of each wiener, cutting to 1/4-inch of opposite side.

title: pasta presto
directions: Toss in the ingredients in order and serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix
flour
and
butter together.
Beat eggs, add sugar and beat
together.
Add to flour mixture.
Add whipping cream and blend well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours (start with cold oven) in	Bundt pan.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool. Sprinkle with 4x sugar.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion on pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs and blend in remaining ingredients. Pour onto pie pan on top of first 3 ingredients.
Bake 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife comes out clean.
Let pie stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 main dish slices.

title: homemade baked beans
directions: Drain 1 can of beans.
Add second can with juice.
Stir in catsup and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Place bacon on top of beans in casserole dish or small roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato delight
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix everything together and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 cup cornflakes or potato chips, crushed. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in egg whites and extract.
Stir in almonds and mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on lightly greased sheet.
Garnish with cherry half.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Remove immediately to wax paper covered area.

title: e z lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add tomato sauce, spaghetti sauce mix and water.
Simmer.
Cook noodles and drain.
Layer noodles and sauce, noodles and sauce until all are layered.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a shaker.

title: the famous cheese ball
directions: Roll diced ham, cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and chives into a ball.
Then roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.
Serves about 20 people.

title: creamy nut fudge
directions: *Add hot water to 1/4 cup Coffee-mate to make 1/2 cup of liquid.

title: dill dip and pumpernickel("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Take 1 pound round pumpernickel (unsliced) and cut top 1/4 or 1/3 off and scoop out inside.
Break up into pieces and put dip into shell at last minute.
Put pieces of bread all around for dipping.
Enjoy!

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place all above (except chicken) in a large 10-inch pot and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place the skinned chicken to cover the bottom of pot.
Continue to simmer for 45 minutes.
Do not cover the pot at any time.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes using package directions, omitting the butter.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Stir in beaten egg, green onion and snipped parsley.
Blend well. Transfer to a well greased 1 quart baking dish.
Dot with 1 tablespoon of butter. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry cream muffins
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar while beating.
Slowly pour in oil.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add alternately with the sour cream to the egg mixture.
Gently fold in blueberries. Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Blend in flour.
Gradually stir in milk and chicken broth over medium heat until mixture thickens or just comes to a boil.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Serves 4.

title: boiled peanuts
directions: Wash peanuts.
Add enough water to cover.
Add salt.
Boil on medium high for about 30 minutes, or when peanuts are tender. (Freeze what is not eaten in freezer bags.)
Take from freezer when ready to eat; place bag in hot water until thawed.

title: mock smoked chicken
directions: Sprinkle soy sauce on chicken; marinate 30 minutes.
In the meantime, combine sugar, sake and miso; mix well!
Pour the mixture over chicken.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender.
(If chicken starts to brown too much, cover with aluminum foil.)
Cool at room temperature or refrigerate. Slice thin and serve.

title: cajun dip
directions: In blender, mash beans with liquid to make a paste.
Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain grease.
Add beans, ketchup, and tabasco.
Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Place in shallow casserole and cover with grated cheese and olives.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: coconut pies
directions: Beat your egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Add to top of pies and brown.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Drain artichokes in food processor. Chop them with garlic.

title: mints
directions: Melt butter over hot water.
Add oil of peppermint to melted butter.
Sift powdered sugar and add to butter mixture.
Add cream.
Mix well. Add food coloring, then press through cake decorator onto waxed paper.
Let dry overnight.
Yield:
150 to 200 mints.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. For the crust, mix the pretzels, butter, and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press this mixture into a 9 by 13-inch pan and bake for 7 minutes. Set aside and allow to cool.

title: pasta in a pot
directions: Cook beef, onion, garlic until brown.
Drain grease.
Put in sauce, undrained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cook shells; drain.
Pour 1/2 shells into deep casserole, cover with 1/2 sauce.
Spread 1/2 sour cream over sauce.
Top with 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 Parmesan.
Repeat second layer.
Bake covered at 350° for 35 minutes.
I use more cheese.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Place oil and vinegar in a quart jar.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate indefinitely (flavor improves with time).
Shake well before serving.
Makes 4 cups dressing.

title: phil's brownies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla, Nestle Quick and eggs in a bowl. Then melt and add butter to mixture and pour back into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In 6-quart pot over high heat, sear meat in olive oil until gray, not brown.
Add 1 quart water; mix well and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Pour off all water; add all seasonings to meat in the 6-quart pot.
Add 1 quart water.
Simmer 30 minutes and adjust taste.
Add cayenne pepper for heat.
Thicken with cornmeal blended with water into a paste and stir well.
Add beans for added flavor and shredded cheese to make it even better.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper then blend in onions, peppers, and mushrooms - set aside.
Butter a 9 x 13 pan and place bread slices in bottom.
Sprinkle browned sausage on bread, then add egg mixture.
Cover pan with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until eggs are set.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese; then bake an additional 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
May use 1/2 c. cheddar cheese and 1/2 c. mozzarella cheese.

title: mustard crumb pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to broil. Mix first 5 ingredients together in a medium bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Pat a portion of this crumb mixture onto both sides of each chop (can be prepared to this point several hours in advance, but keep refrigerated). Place chops onto a broiler pan, 4 inches from heat source. Broil, turning once with spatula, until golden brown (3 minutes per side). Adjust oven to 350°. Bake chops 15 to 20 minutes. Serve Immediately.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Spread 1/2-inch in 8 x 10-inch pan. Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cream together egg and mushroom soup.
Cut up squash; cook until tender and all the water has cooked out of them.
Add margarine (1/2 of margarine), salt, pepper, onion and mushroom soup with egg mixture.
Let cook a little longer.
Pour into casserole dish (spray with Pam).
Crush enough Ritz crackers to cover top and melt margarine (1/2 stick) and pour over top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for about 2 hours.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl.
Add pecans.
Combine the milk, butter and eggs in a bowl.
Next, add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients and mix until just combined.
Spoon batter into well-buttered muffin tins.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: apple yam casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish; drain and slice yams and put into casserole.
Add pie filling; stir slightly, don't mix.
Top with butter cut in slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread sausage in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients in bowl and pour over sausage.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with picante sauce for different taste.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend at low speed. Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan
Cool cake upright in pan for 15 minutes before removing.

title: molasses crinkles(like "grandma's molasses cookies")
directions: Mix together thoroughly first four ingredients.
Sift rest of ingredients together and stir in first mixture gradually.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls sized like large walnuts and flatten slightly.
Dip tops into cold water, then into sugar.
Place, sugared side up, 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until set but not hard.
Cool and store in covered container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut in small pieces.
Saute celery, pepper and onion in margarine. Add stuffing. Combine chicken, mushroom soup and chicken soup. Add 2 cups broth.
Use half of bread mix in bottom of baking dish. Pour chicken mix on top of bread mix and top with rest of the bread mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday cranberries and apples
directions: Mix cranberries, sugar and apples.
Put in Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Mix dry ingredients and put on top of first mixture.
Cut 1/2 stick of butter and put on top of dry mixture. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Goes great with poultry, pork or beef.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix jello and pineapple in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and let cool.
Add buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in container and sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: ruby's peanut butter fudge
directions: Rub stick of margarine around sides and bottom of warm saucepan.
Add sugar, evaporated milk, and margarine.
Cook to hard-boil stage.
Add marshmallow cream, vanilla, and peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into buttered cookie sheet (with 1/2-inch sides).

title: peppered corn
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Chop tomatoes and add to onion and bell pepper.
Add drained whole corn, cream-style corn and Shoe Peg corn.
Cook on medium heat, stirring often, for about 15 to 20 minutes, until slightly thickened.

title: honey fudge
directions: Dissolve sugar in milk and honey.
Add grated chocolate, butter or butter substitute and salt.
Stir until well blended. Cover until boiling point is reached.
Boil to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Cool to room temperature.
Add flavorings.
Beat until mixture is thick, creamy and will hold its shape when dropped from a teaspoon.

title: mom's chocolate chip cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add pudding mix, eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cauliflower with almonds
directions: Prepare cauliflower, then steam until tender, about 20 minutes. Saute remaining ingredients in butter or margarine until almonds are golden and crumbs crisp.
Pour over cauliflower when ready to use.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Work together, then pat into cake pan and bake at 350° until brown (about 15 minutes).
Then set out to cool.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix salt, eggs, broth and butter and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.

title: english apple pie
directions: Beat butter and brown sugar until pale and fluffy.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and water until smooth and thick. Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in a 9-inch pie plate.
Mix sugar with remaining cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan topping over apples in blobs.
Bake on lowest rack in preheated 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: molasses pie
directions: Beat eggs; mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and sorghum.
Add eggs and butter.
Heat thoroughly.
Bake in uncooked pie shell in 450° oven for first 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate.
Cook until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches
directions: Cook, covered, 6 hours on top of stove or in oven at 325° until meat is fork-tender and easy to shred.
Keep covered entire time of cooking.
Add water occasionally to keep from drying out. Serve on hard rolls.

title: cold pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool macaroni.
Mix in chopped vegetables.
Cook other ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Cool this mixture.
Pour over pasta and chopped vegetables and chill well.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop into greased muffin pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: wesson oil rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Mix other ingredients in order
given.
Brush oil on top and cover with clean towel. Let rise
until
double
in
size.
Knead for 6 to 10 times on dough board.
Add flour as needed.

title: oatmeal bread(no-knead)
directions: Combine water, oatmeal, shortening, molasses and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast; mix well.
Blend in eggs.
Add flour; mix well.
Dough will be softer than kneaded dough.
Place in greased bowl and cover.
Store in cold place at least 2 hours or until needed.
On well-floured board, shape dough into 2 loaves to fit 9 x 5-inch pan and 12 x 4-inch pan.
Pans should be greased and floured.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size about 2 hours.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cool on racks.

title: short cut lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off excess fat and pour tomato sauce into skillet.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese and noodles in casserole. Pour meat sauce over and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Put Cheddar cheese over top and bake until hot.

title: q's chicken puff pastry
directions: *May be bought already prepared.
If mix is bought, be sure you have all necessary ingredients listed on package necessary to make sauce.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in a large Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in Dutch oven.
Drain bacon on paper towels. Add onion and celery to drippings.
Saute until tender, stirring frequently.
Drain.
Add bouillon, tomatoes and next 5 ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes.
Add lettuce and cook 2 minutes or until lettuce wilts. Top with bacon and croutons.
Serve immediately.
Yields 5 cups.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten egg yolk together with milk and vanilla.
Alternate blackberries and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.
Bake in tube pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Mix with chopped onion, pepper, cheese, eggs and mushroom soup.
Top with cracker crumbs or stuffing mix.
Bake until brown.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Saute ground meat and onion until brown; drain.
Add carrots, mushrooms, tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and rosemary.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine broth and flour until smooth.
Add to meat and cook 5 minutes more.
Boil potatoes.
Drain and mash with margarine and milk.
Add parsley.
Place meat in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until potatoes are brown.

title: easter pound cake(pizelle cake)
directions: Grease and flour bundt pan. Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil. Mix for 5 mins.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and mash avocados.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Best if made the day before to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with taco chips.

title: sweet potato - apple bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray Pyrex dish with Pam, 8 x 8-inch. Heat skim milk, water, spices and raisins in a pan on top of the stove.
Add sweet potatoes and simmer, uncovered, until tender, about 20 minutes.
Mash this mixture together when potatoes are tender.
Stir in nonfat yogurt.
If using apples in the recipe, slice thin and spread layer on the bottom of Pyrex dish.
Top with sweet potato mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: eleanor's pumpkin pie
directions: Put pumpkin in a large bowl.
Add sugar, beaten eggs, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add milk gradually and beat two minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then 375° about an hour or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: mini meatball and  bell pepper soup
directions: Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onions and peppers and cook, stirring often, 10 minutes or until vegetables are soft.
Add garlic, oregano, and basil.
Stir until garlic is fragrant.
Stir in tomato juice and water, and stirring occasionally, bring to boil.
Stir in pasta; cook 12 to 15 minutes or until pasta is firm-tender.
Stir in meatballs and canned tomatoes, salt and pepper, simmer 5 minutes or until meatballs are hot.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Slice apples into crust.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.
Cut butter into sugar and flour.
Crumble on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, covered with foil, and then bake 30 minutes after removing foil.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese. Add sugar slowly to creamed mixture.
Add cold water, coconut flavoring and coconut flakes.
Pour into well greased and floured tube cake pan.
Place in cold oven and turn to 275° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp and cheese soup
directions: Cook bouillon, water, beer, celery, onion and shrimp for 20 minutes. Add potatoes and peas and carrots. Cook until tender. Add cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted and soup is hot.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, flour, oil or applesauce, water and egg or egg substitute.
Add nuts, chocolate chips or whatever you wish to enhance the particular cookie you're creating.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until edges just begin to brown. Cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute, then place on cookie rack.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients (cake mix, Jell-O and sugar). Add oil, water and eggs and mix. Add strawberries and beat until thoroughly blended (about 2 minutes). Cook at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Do not overcook.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut in small pieces.
Mix chicken, soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine crushed crackers and butter or margarine and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well.
Will keep for several days.

title: oatmeal jam bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Combine all ingredients, except jam; mix well.
Reserve 3/4 cup oats mixture; press remaining mixture onto bottom of prepared dish.
Bake 10 minutes.
Spread jam evenly over partially-baked base to within 1/2 inch of edge of pan; sprinkle with reserved oats mixture.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Chill 2 hours or more. Roll into 1-inch balls.
Refrigerate.
Melt chocolate bits and wax in double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls and set on waxed paper. Refrigerate to set.
Makes 60 to 70.

title: peach waldorf salad
directions: In bowl combine chopped peaches, celery, walnuts, mayonnaise, lemon juice and salt (if you like).
Mix well.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Rinse lettuce in cold water.
Top with marshmallows. Serves 6.

title: garlic-sour cream noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to instructions; drain and rinse.
Toss with margarine until melted, then add sour cream and seasonings. Serves 6.

title: spicy italian roast
directions: Season roast with garlic salt (I prefer powder).
Place in crock-pot.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Combine seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Pour over all.
Cover and cook on low 10 - 12 hours (high:
4 - 6 hours).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: brown sugar pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar and water to a syrup.
Add butter.
Make a batter of white sugar, flour, baking powder, raisins and water. Pour syrup into baking dish.
Then pour in batter.
Do not stir. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken picante
directions: In skillet in hot oil, cook chicken about 10 minutes or until brown.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, lemon juice and paprika. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: thick cream sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour and mix well.
Add cold milk slowly, stirring until smooth and creamy.
Add salt and pepper and boil about 3 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Scald milk. Add margarine. Heat oysters in own liquid until edges curl. Add to the milk. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve hot with crackers.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In mixing bowl, add beef, rice, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and 1/3 can of tomato soup; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup water to remaining soup; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into balls.
(I use an ice cream scoop to shape meatballs.)
Place in frypan.
Pour tomato soup/water mixture over meatballs.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix milk and flour; add to potatoes in pan on stove top. Using medium heat, bring to bubble.
Add margarine and stir until melted.
Place potatoes and all into greased casserole and put in oven at 350°, covered, for 3/4 hour.
Remove cover; test potatoes for doneness and let brown on top.

title: bird's nest cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add yolks, then flour and vanilla. Chill well.
Roll into small balls.
Beat egg whites slightly, roll balls in egg white and then nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and make thumbprint in the cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove and fill tops with jelly.
Return to oven for 10 more minutes or until light brown.

title: austrian ecstasy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 1 1/2-inch) round cake pans.
Line with wax paper and grease paper.
In 3-quart saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and butter; remove from heat.
With wooden spoon, beat in eggs.
Stir in sugar, milk, vanilla and salt. Add flour and baking powder.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into pans.	Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.	Cool in pans on wire racks for five minutes.
Remove from pans.
Remove paper immediately.
Cool completely on wire racks.

title: french dressing
directions: Place salt and mustard in a bowl and beat in vinegar, thus allowing salt to dissolve.
Add oil gradually and season with pepper or place all ingredients in a covered jar and shake vigorously.
Store in refrigerator and use just before serving salad.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Add egg yolks and beat good.
Add lemon extract and beat, then add 2 cups flour and baking powder.
Mix pineapple, cherries, pecans and 2 cups flour and add to first mixture.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Let stand overnight.
Pile gently in pan and cook at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Soak black-eyed peas overnight.
Put water 2 1/2 inches above peas.

title: sausage cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10 1/2-inch skillet or 2-quart baking dish; set aside.

title: sausage mushroom quiche
directions: Brown sausage slowly until liquid is cooked off.
Drain grease, add mushrooms and cook 5 minutes.
Add parsley.
Beat eggs and blend in cheese and cream.
Stir in salt.
Pour over mushrooms and sausage.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes in pastry shell.
Let stand 10 minutes before cooking.
Enjoy!

title: molasses cookies("my prize-winning recipe")
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add carrots and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over dry mixture, stirring quickly.
Place on medium hot burner.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Use as hot sauce over desserts.
Delicious on ice cream, warm or cold.
Store in refrigerator.

title: torture cake
directions: Bake as directed in 4 round cake pans.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Hidden Valley Ranch mix together.
Roll into a ball.
Roll the ball in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate, and serve.

title: saucy chicken and noodles
directions: In oblong baking dish, arrange chicken.
Combine soup and milk; spoon over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serve with noodles.

title: savory swiss style eggs
directions: Mix together.
You may add mushrooms, ham, bacon or sausage. Mix all together in a large bowl.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: frost on the pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl combine frosting, sour cream, pumpkin, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Pour into crust and spread with remaining whipped topping.

title: oriental vegetables
directions: Soak vegetables in water for a few minutes.
Melt butter in electric skillet and add vegetables.
Cook, covered, at medium heat for 15 minutes.

title: pasties from sweden
directions: Roll dough into circles.
Layer carrots, potatoes, meat, and onions.
Dot with oleo on top.
Salt and pepper.
Bring up sides of dough.
Pinch on top.
Bake on sheet at 400° for 30 minutes, then bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Can bake and freeze.)
Top each with gravy before serving.
Can use canned.

title: mexican lake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and nuts.
Set aside.
Mix together crushed pineapple and baking soda.
After fizzle stops, mix in rest of mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy chocolate fondue
directions: Heat sweetened condensed milk, milk and butter in medium saucepan over Med-Low, until butter is melted.
Add chocolate morsels; stir until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Serve immediately in fondue pot or serving dish to keep warm.
Serve as a dip with marshmallows, cubes of angel food cake, pound cake, pieces of fruit such as apples, pears, strawberries, mandarin oranges, pineapple, bananas and seedless grapes.

title: mochac(mahchack, hungarian dish)
directions: Chop onion and cabbage and fry in oil on medium heat.
Slice sausage into bite size pieces and add to cabbage.
Cook noodles in chicken cubes for 45 minutes; drain and fry in oil until lightly browned, stirring often.
Combine all ingredients.
(Try with Louisiana hot sauce.)
Serves 3 firemen or 5 regular appetites.

title: boiled cake(old family recipe)
directions: Bring coffee, raisins, spices, oleo, sugar and salt to a boil. Cool overnight or enough to add dry ingredients.
Add nuts and cherries last.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on oven.
Done when tested with a toothpick and it comes out clean.

title: one meal hot dish
directions: Grease a baking dish.
On bottom of dish place a layer of sliced potatoes.
Put tomato soup on top with water.
Mix tomato soup and water together.
Then pour over the top.
Bake for 2 hours in a 300° oven.
Amount of ground meat will be about 1 pound or a little more.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Crush and drain berries; keep juice. Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups. Bring juice mixture to a boil. Add gelatin. Dissolve and cool.
Add strawberries and sugar.
Whip the cream and blend into mixture. Chill until set.

title: tomato, onion and pepper salad
directions: Place
tomato slices on a platter.
Arrange onion rings on top.
Garnish
with
green	pepper	slices.
Sprinkle with basil, salt
and pepper, oregano, garlic and cheese.
Pour oil slowly over all.

title: mother's forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Beat in salt and vanilla.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Do not open door until oven is cool (overnight).
Yields 4 to 6 dozen.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish or roaster and bake at 300 for 3 1/2 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Add flour, baking powder and salt and mix well.
Combine milk and egg and pour into flour mixture and stir until just smooth. Add corn and stir.
Drop by tablespoons into deep hot fat and fry 3 to 5 minutes, turning until fritters are well browned on all sides.
Drain on paper towel.

title: strawberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, tapioca and salt together.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Mix strawberries, rhubarb and sugar mixture together and place in pie pan.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.

title: fruit delight
directions: Note: 7-Up may be used in place of water.

title: honey cookies-russia(medianyky)
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Sift the flour, spices, sugar, and baking powder together, blending well. Add the eggs, honey, and orange peel to make a soft dough. On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough to about 1/2 inch thick. Cut into shapes with cookie cutter and place on lightly greased

or non-stick cookie sheet. Brush each cookie with the egg wash glaze. Place one almond half in the center of each cookie and sprinkle with the coarse sugar. Bake 10-15 minutes or until done. Cool on wire racks.

title: creamy brussels sprouts
directions: Halve large fresh Brussels sprouts.
In a medium saucepan cook fresh sprouts, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes, or until crisp-tender.
Drain and remove from pan (or cook frozen sprouts according to package directions; drain and remove from pan; halve any large sprouts).
In the same saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender.
In a bowl combine milk, sour cream, flour, mustard and salt.
Add to saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in Brussels sprouts; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: catherine howell's copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in slightly salted water until tender, but firm. Drain and rinse with water.
Mix soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring well.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper. Refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 2/3 cup white sugar to deep brown in iron skillet.

Add boiling water. Cook until like a syrup. Cool. Cream butter; add sugar and cream well. Add burnt sugar and beaten egg yolks. Beat well; add dry ingredients. Add milk, water, vanilla and stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 400° oven. Makes 3 layers.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a glass casserole and cover with buttered bread cubes.
Cook in oven at 350° about 50 minutes, until bread is browned and liquid absorbed.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break 2 slices bread into small pieces.

Mix thoroughly with 1 lightly beaten egg, 1 tablespoon mayonnaise, 1 teaspoon seafood seasoning, 1 teaspoon parsley flakes, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce and 2 teaspoons baking powder.
Combine with 1 pound crab meat, flaked.
Shape into 8 cakes.
Fry in small amount of hot fat.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Rinse in cold water.
Chop tomatoes and cucumbers.
Add all ingredients to pasta and mix well. Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour cooked green beans in baking dish.
Mix with cream of mushroom soup.
Spread melted cream cheese over top, then pour cooked rice over cheese.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: alabama baked beans
directions: Place beans and onion in baking dish.
Mix molasses, catsup, brown sugar and water; add to beans.
Place slices of bacon on top of beans (if bacon is pushed down into beans it will not brown too much).
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: cheese and sausage balls
directions: Mix together thoroughly; roll into balls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Put ice cream in large bowl to soften.
Set aside.
Melt oleo and crush crackers in a 9 x 13-pan.
Add melted oleo and mix well. Save 1 cup or 1 1/2 cups to sprinkle on top.
Press the rest into bottom of pan.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornmeal, milk and 2 eggs and bake in oven.
Do not brown or cook
hard
for
it needs to be easy to crumble.
Let cool before mixing with grits (can be instant grits, mixed and cooled), cold
biscuits (canned biscuits can be used), bread, onion and celery.
Mix with chicken broth.
Beat eggs; stir in well.
Bake in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Will serve about 20 people.

title: quesadilla
directions: On each flour tortilla, sprinkle portions of both cheeses and chopped chilies.
Fold tortillas in halves and place on large baking sheet.
Brush tops of each with melted butter.
Place in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until tops are golden brown. Cut into triangular quarters.
Serve with guacamole and/or sour cream.
Add grilled chicken (fry chunks of chicken in Italian salad dressing on stove) and onions (cut up and cooked with chicken).

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator for up to 3 weeks.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: rohliky(crescent rolls)
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup water with teaspoon sugar.
Combine hot milk, shortening and salt and cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour. Add yeast and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in remaining flour and knead lightly 5 to 8 minutes.
Cover and let rise until double, then divide dough into thirds.
Roll each into 9-inch circle.
Divide circle like pie and roll big end first so point is on outside. Arrange rolls point down on greased cookie sheet.
Curve slightly like a crescent.
Brush with melted butter.
Before baking, beat an egg with a little water and sprinkle poppy seed on them.
Cover and let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Mixture will be very thick.
Flour wax paper and roll out dough to desired thickness.
Cut out.
Place on greased cookie sheet at 325° for approximately 8 minutes or until desired brownness.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Bring to boil the oil, vinegar and seasonings.
Sprinkle sugar, don't stir.
Let sit for 4 hours.

title: chimichangas
directions: Allow tortillas to thaw while preparing the filling.
In a saucepan, combine tomato sauce, cooked meat, onion, chili powder, garlic powder, cocoa, cumin, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to simmer 10 minutes.
Allow filling to cool.
Lay tortilla on a clean surface and divide the filling evenly in the center of each tortilla.
Fold each tortilla like an envelope and secure with a toothpick.
Deep fry on medium heat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel and keep warm, uncovered, on a warming tray or in low oven until ready to serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs, oil and vanilla, stirring until moistened.
Add pineapple, pecans, black walnuts and bananas; stir.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove and cool on wire racks.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In
a
bowl,
stir
together
the flours, baking powder, baking soda
and
salt; set aside.
In another bowl, beat sugar and butter.
Add
eggs, one at a time.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Add flour mixture and banana alternately to sugar mixture. Fold in chopped
nuts.
Put
batter
into
a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Make pie crust.
Beat eggs and the rest and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts on top.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp and water chestnuts
directions: You will also need toothpicks.

title: audra's broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: doris' vinegar oil cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together three times.
In large mixing bowl, make a well in the middle of the dry ingredients and add the first 3 liquid items to it, then add the two cups of cold water over all of it.
Mix well, but do not beat.

title: mom's vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly with mixer.
Pour into ice cream
maker can. Add condensed milk and stir well. Add milk to fill line on can.
Stir and freeze.

title: pan roasted chicken with garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a baking dish, mix garlic, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, water, 2 tablespoons parsley flakes, melted butter, pepper and cayenne.

title: chilli mac(if you like chilli, you'll love chilli mac.)
directions: In a pan, boil the pork until tender; drain and dice.
Place in a large skillet or pan and add onions, mushrooms, salt, pepper, celery, bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Add thickening made from melted butter and flour mixed together well.
Cook 2 minutes, then serve on top of cooked rice and top with chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Slice one roll of cookie dough between 1/4 and 1/2-inch thick. Spread slices on the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Push all together to form one.

title: roast pork and sauerkraut
directions: Slice apples and onions into crock-pot (or Dutch oven).
Add a small pork roast (pork shoulder is cheap and good or fresh pork butt).
Add sauerkraut and several tablespoons of brown sugar. Cook slowly overnight (add a little water if there is not enough juice from kraut).
Cook until meat falls off bone.
I cook this overnight in a crock-pot about 12 hours.

title: green beans creole
directions: Steam green beans until tender-crisp.
Combine with other ingredients in saucepan.
Cook 15 more minutes.
Contains 0 fat grams per serving.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Press firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: meat loaf-stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seeds from peppers.
Immerse in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Pour 1 cup spaghetti sauce into the bottom of a shallow baking dish; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine meat loaf, rice, onion, chopped green pepper and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Cook and stir over medium heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Stuff each pepper with meat loaf mixture; place on sauce in baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with the cheese and let stand until melted.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: bacon-burger turnovers
directions: Saute onion and butter.
In another pan, fry strips of bacon. Drain the grease and add the onion.
Next add the ground beef, salt and pepper.
Add the 2 tablespoons flour and cook over medium heat until brown.
Add soup; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add the sour cream and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cool the meat mixture.
Make a crust with the flour, shortening, salt and water.
Roll out and cut 5-inch circles and fill with rounded teaspoonful of meat on circle.
Fold over and brush with oleo.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: cauliflower-bacon salad
directions: Mix sugar into mayo.
Combine all other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: tortilla appetizer pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread over tortillas and roll up. Refrigerate a few hours and cut into slices.
Serve with salsa.

title: "special" french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Cover and blend on high speed about 25 seconds.
Serve on salads.
Store leftover dressing in covered container in refrigerator.

title: lincoln highway salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and keep chilled until ready to use.

title: quick chili-rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add spices, corn, green peppers, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is done. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together with 1/2 pint sour cream. Place in refrigerator to chill well before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars, then egg.
Add peanut butter and hot water.
Sift soda to flour and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and press with tines of a fork. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Mix well with fork. Add shortening (do not use oil, lard, oleo or butter).
Mix with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat water, vinegar and egg. Combine 2 mixtures, stirring with fork until moistened.
Divide dough in 5 portions.
With hands, shape each portion in a flat round patty ready for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic or waxed paper.
Chill at least 1/2 hour.
When ready to roll, lightly flour both sides of patty and place on lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Cover rolling pin with stocking net and rub with flour. Roll from center, keeping pastry round until desired size.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Place margarine, water, shortening and cocoa in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Stir well and add to other mixture.
Bake in greased and floured oblong pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Bring to a boil broccoli, water, chicken bouillon cubes, celery and onion and simmer 10 minutes.
Add milk and water and return to a boil.
Add butter, flour, milk, Cheez Whiz and simmer until hot and mixed well.

title: macaroni and cheese 2
directions: Boil macaroni for 12 minutes.
Drain water.
Add salt, pepper, eggs and margarine and mix, then add cheese and milk and mix.
Put in glass meat loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together.
Pour into greased and wax papered 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool.
Frost and sprinkle with coconut.
Cut into squares.

title: cheddar turkey bake
directions: Prepare rice
according to package; add to rice, minced onion, while
in
boiling	water.	Combine peas, turkey, soup, milk, mustard
and salt.	Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 10 x 6
x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Mix crackers and butter and sprinkle on	top
of
casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: candy coated nuts
directions: Cook sugar, brown sugar and sour cream to soft ball stage. Add vanilla.
Beat until thickened.
Add nuts.
Turn out onto buttered plate or buttered wax paper.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix milk, margarine, sugar, coconut and vanilla together and make into mounds or small shaped balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in
double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip mounds into chocolate mixture.	Let
tips
of
mounds
show.
Makes 5 pounds of candy.

title: clinton chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter. Combine with remaining ingredients except cheese; turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beer batter(used for years!)
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and stir in beer; add to flour and stir only until blended.
Add margarine and let stand 1 hour. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into mixture.
Great for shrimp and fish pieces or almost anything.
Deep fat fry.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Heat broccoli in 1 cup salted water that is boiling.
Cook 5 minutes and drain.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese and put in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper 15 seconds in blender.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake and set aside. When cool, pull into pieces. Then put cake on bottom of bowl, one layer, then a layer of pudding, then a layer of cherry pie filling, then a layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts. Keep doing this until all used up. Keep in the refrigerator.

title: hearty vegetable soup(12 quart pot)
directions: Fill a 12-quart pot 1/2 full with water.
Add pepper, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Boil chicken and ribs for 1 hour.
Add water while cooking.
Leave stock in pot.
Debone meats and cut into bite size pieces.
Dice potatoes.
Cut okra into 1-inch pieces.
Add other ingredients (chopped) to stock, along with meat.
Cook for 5 or 6 hours on low heat.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and milk well.
Mix together the flour, sugar and nutmeg and add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in cut up rhubarb. Pour into pastry-lined pie pan and dot with butter or margarine. Cover with top pastry.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: roast and potato bake
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Roast at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon off fat.
Arrange potatoes around meat. Combine soup; pour over meat and potatoes.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours more or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake until the cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raisin scones
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Knead lightly and pat down onto a floured board into a 3/4-inch thick circle.
Cut into 8 wedges and place individually on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm with butter and homemade jam.

title: luann's dessert
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Add salt, pepper, chili mix, 1/2 mustard and 1/2 ketchup while browning meat.
Drain good.
Put remaining chili powder, mustard and ketchup and simmer. Add the tomato juice and simmer about 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: herbed spaghetti squash
directions: Pierce squash 6 to 8 times with a fork.
Place squash in a layer of paper towel in the microwave; microwave, uncovered, on High 15 minutes or until soft to touch, turning squash over every 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine oil and garlic in a large bowl; microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Stir in basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cut squash in half; remove seeds.
Using a fork, remove spaghetti like strands.
Combine squash and oil mixture; toss gently.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in round cake pans (two).
When cool, place 1 cake in bottom of bowl.
Spread half of the prepared pudding on top.
Add Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle with candy and nuts.
Layer again with cake, pudding and Cool Whip; sprinkle top with candy and nuts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake the layers. Take 1 layer and crumble it in a bowl. Put first box of strawberries over this.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
