Beat eggs lightly and add mayonnaise, mushroom soup, cheese and onion.
Put in casserole.
For topping, melt margarine in saucepan.
Add crumbled Ritz crackers.
Spoon over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: baked coon
directions: Boil a cut up raccoon until tender.
Drain off the broth and use to make cornbread dressing.
Salt and pepper the raccoon well and bake in a moderately hot oven with the cornbread dressing until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done.
Add salt.
Drain well. Place 1/2 broccoli in casserole.
Cover with water chestnuts.
Add 1/2 of soup.
Cover with remaining broccoli.
Add remaining soup. Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: queen elizabeth ii cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates and soda.
Let stand. Mix sugar, butter, egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder, nuts and salt.
Add to date mixture and bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan for 35 minutes in a moderate oven.
Boil the cream, butter and light brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Spread on cake.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli with onion and drain.
Brown sausage and drain. Combine cheese and soup over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Add broccoli mixture and meat.
Serve with any kind of chips.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix wet ingredients together. Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix
together
the
softened
butter,
cream cheese and sugar. Beat
until
creamy.
Add eggs; beat until well mixed, then gradually add flour, then vanilla.	Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: italian hot dog
directions: Cook hot dog to your satisfaction.
Heat sauce 1 minute or until hot on stove top.
Put cheese on bottom of bun.
Place hot dog on cheese and pour sauce over hot dog.
Serves 1.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Shape dough into balls and roll in 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: beulah's lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on the package.
In a baking dish, place a layer of noodles, a layer of Ricotta cheese, layer of spaghetti sauce and a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Continue until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: brussels sprouts with almonds
directions: Remove dark outer leaves of sprouts and trim stem ends. Halve, if desired.

title: chocolate buttercream frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat for 10 minutes until light and fluffy.
Yields frosting for 2 to 3 cakes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Mix and work all together.
Roll out.
Makes about 26 pie crusts for your filling.

title: dill pickles
directions: Prepare cucumbers as you like them:
spears, slices, whole.
In bottom of each quart jar, put one whole garlic clove, 1 sprig of fresh dill and 1/2 teaspoon of alum.
Fill jar with cucumbers, packing tightly.
Place one more garlic clove and 1 sprig of fresh dill on top of jar.
Fill with prepared water*.
Process by home canning method.
Let set for 3 months before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix everything together.
Add Miracle Whip 1/4 cup at a time until creamy.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll in small balls.
Bake for 45 minutes at 300°.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: chili(very good)
directions: Brown meat and onion in pan. Drain all grease. Add chili powder, tomatoes and beans.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: herring apple appetizer
directions: Drain herring; cut into bite size pieces, if necessary.
Blend sour cream with herring and other ingredients.
Toss to blend well. Chill before serving.
Serve as an appetizer with crackers or on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: barbecued sauerkraut and weiners(great for a campout)
directions: Cook the ingredients (except sauerkraut and wieners) for 7 to 8 minutes, then add sauerkraut and wieners.
On medium heat, cook for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Crush Ritz crackers while they are still in the sleeve. Melt the butter and add to the cracker crumbs, mix well and set aside. Spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam cooking spray, add potatoes and onions. Mix together sour cream and chicken soup with the cheddar cheese. Pour over the potato mixture. Add the Ritz cracker topping. Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then uncover and bake another 1/2 hour or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: In a large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Add sweetened condensed milk until smooth; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared crust; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.
Cool and serve with whipped topping or plain.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add onions on top 5 minutes before removing from oven.

title: hot fried beef strips
directions: Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across grain into bite size strips.
In bowl combine onion, soy sauce, 1 tablespoon oil, sugar, garlic and hot pepper sauce.
Add beef strips and toss to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes at room temperature.
Fry in skillet in oil quickly, using a small amount at a time.

title: beef brisket with potatoes on the half-shell with sour
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Wipe the brisket with a clean, damp cloth and season it with salt.
Roast it in a deep roasting pan until golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Add about 2 cups of water to the pan or just enough to keep the roast from sticking and burning on the bottom.
Sprinkle the roast with freshly ground pepper.
Add the thyme and bay leaves.
Cover and reduce the heat to 325°.
Cook until the meat is tender, another 2 to 2 1/2 hours (this will vary with the size and grade of the brisket).

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In a large bowl, mix well the ground beef, onion, celery, chili sauce, egg, pepper, half (1 1/3 cups) of potato flakes, milk and salt.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: crab artichoke casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise and half and half until smooth and add cubed bread.
Fold next 7 ingredients into this mixture.
Pour into a slightly greased, shallow two-quart casserole.
Cover and chill overnight.
Combine soft bread crumbs and oleo.
Stir and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake one hour at 325° or until bubbly. Yields 8 servings.

title: gaylene's cranberry salad
directions: Boil berries in water and sugar until all berries burst open. Remove from fire.
Add gelatin and marshmallows.
Stir until melted and dissolved.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well. Chill.

title: cupcake frosting
directions: Mix ingredients.
Will easily frost 2 dozen cupcakes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: jerry's chicken special
directions: Place slices of bacon in baking dish.
Spread rice on top of bacon.
Lay chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle with oregano, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup mixed with water over chicken.
Sprinkle freely with paprika.
Seal with foil and place in 300° oven.
Cook two hours.
Do not peek.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour and salt.
Stir in milk
slowly.
Cook
over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Add chicken, lemon
and sage.
Shape into croquettes.
Beat eggs and water together.
Dip croquettes
into egg mixture.
Roll in crumbs. Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Heat pan.
Add oil and fry onions until brown.
Add cold rice and saute.
Add eggs, seasoned with soy sauce and salt.
Saute until done.
For variety, add 2 cups chopped, cooked meat (bacon, ham, shrimp or chicken), chopped pepper or peanuts (shelled and roasted).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding one egg at a time. Bake in	a
Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
When cool, drizzle with lemon juice and powdered sugar glaze.

title: kielbasa stew
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except broth, water and seasoning. Place in 5-quart pot and then add water, broth and seasonings. Cook on high for 4 to 5 hours.
Check several times.
May not take as long, depending on size of diced and sliced potatoes.
May cook on low-medium all day if desired.

title: baked yam and apple casserole
directions: Scrub yams and prick with a fork.
Microwave on High until not quite tender, about 8 minutes.
(If using canned yams, do not microwave.)
Let cool, then peel and sliced 1/4 inch thick.
Peel and core apples and slice into 1/4-inch rings.
Spray shallow casserole with vegetable spray.
In layers, alternately place yams, apples, margarine, brown sugar and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover, baste with juices and cook about 5 to 10 minutes more, until yams and apples are tender and lightly browned.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta as directed on bag.
Cool.
Mix all remaining ingredients with pasta.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
To taste, saute chopped onion, green pepper and celery in a little broth until tender.
Put chicken, spaghetti, green pepper, celery and Velveeta cheese in bowl.
Add mushroom soup and chicken soup to chicken mixture.
Mix.
Add water as needed.
May add pimentos or red pepper for color.

title: texas chili
directions: Prepare in a Dutch oven.
Saute vegetables in 1 tablespoon oil until onion is clear.
Remove from pan.
Add remaining oil and brown beef, one-half at a time.
Return all vegetables to the pan. Add the spices and tomatoes and sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender and tomatoes have boiled apart.
Serve topped with chopped raw onions, grated Monterey Jack cheese and a small dab of sour cream on each bowl.
Serves about 12.

title: mom's applesauce cupcakes
directions: Cream Shortening, Sugar and Eggs together in a bowl.
Add 1 c. Applesauce.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to mix stirring until batter is smooth.
Add Raisins to taste (make it as lumpy as you like).
Bake in cup cake tins at 375 degrees for about 20 mins. Yield:

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over corn flakes and peanuts. Mix until coated.
Pour into pan.
While still warm, cut into squares.

title: simple, delicious, fresh apple dip
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat cheese and brown sugar until completely mixed and smooth.
Chill at least 2 hours. Quarter apples, then slice each quarter into thirds.
When ready to serve, spread cheese mix in shallow bowl, then sprinkle chopped peanuts on top of cheese mixture.

title: ravioli with walnut sauce
directions: Cook ravioli according to directions. Meanwhile, in a skillet on medium heat, melt butter. Add walnuts (sugar coat and roast first, if you have time) and garlic cloves. About 1 minute or so later, add scallions, thinly sliced.
Add fresh parsley or basil. (Spinach is a nice addition as well.) Sprinkle liberally with cheese. Salt and pepper to taste. Put over ravioli.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Blend all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute. Scrape sides and mix on medium 2 minutes more. Pour batter into a greased and floured pan. Bake for 45 to 47 minutes in a 350° oven. Cool for 20 minutes. Invert onto serving plate. Prepare glaze.

title: special baked beans
directions: Rinse beans well.
Put in large saucepan.
Add water to cover. Cover and bring to boil (medium heat).
Boil gently 2 minutes. Remove; let stand covered 1 hour.
Add ham bone and additional water to cover.
Return to medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Add water as needed to keep beans covered.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Drain beans, reserving liquid.
Put beans into a 4-quart baking dish.
Add sugar, molasses, salt, mustard, ginger, pepper, catsup and 1 cup of bean liquid.
Stir to mix well.
If needed more bean liquid to cover beans.
Bake, covered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Uncover; bake 1 hour to brown a little.
Makes 12 large servings.
Can refrigerate 4 days or freeze.

title: potato-cheese scallop
directions: Butter 1-1/2 quart casserole.
Blend Cheese Soup and Milk. Layer into casserole beginning with Potatoes, add Onions, add Sauce.
Dot with Butter and Paprika.
Cover and bake at 350 for 60 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with 1 onion and 2 stalks celery.
Cool, debone and save broth.
Cook egg noodles in broth.
Saute 1 onion, 3 stalks celery and green pepper in butter.
Add parsley, garlic and poultry seasoning.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Put
foil
around pan for baking.
Take large container and chop
fruit
fine, then chop nuts and pour over fruit; put coconut, sugar, flavoring and then pour melted butter over and mix.
Break eggs to
side of bowl and beat and mix.
Add flour and mix until wet.
Bake
in wax paper lined pan at 275° until done, about 2 1/2
hours.
Do
not
overcook.
Put foil on top until about 30 minutes before done.
Remove and let cool.

title: chicken dish
directions: Layer casserole dish (9 x 13-inch) with beef slices.
Wrap breast pieces with bacon and lay on beef slices.
Pour soup over chicken and bake in oven.
If you bake this for Sunday dinner, put in slow oven (200° to 250°) while you're at church.
When baked at other times, bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour (until chicken is done).

title: jelly jewels
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degree. Grease cookie sheet.

title: hors d'oeuvre dip
directions: Grind onion and braunschweiger together.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise into meat well.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours and then roll in nuts.

title: red roquefort dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend for 5 minutes. Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as you remove from oven, pour can of condensed milk over cake and let cool.
Pour caramel topping over cake.
In food processor or blender, process candy bars and nuts until coarse crumbs.
Spread 3/4 of candy and nut mixture over caramel topping.
Spread whipped topping over this, then sprinkle remaining candy/nut mixture over whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: jarlsberg dip
directions: Mix ingredients all together. Bake in an oven-safe dish at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Spread on crackers or pieces of French bread.

title: robert's stir-fry conglomeration
directions: I cook the pork, then beef and chicken.
I remove the meat from wok and wipe it out, then start cooking the rest in about the order they are in.
Serve over rice, pancit canton noodles or bean threads.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat, then add sour milk and bananas.
Add flour, soda and salt to mixture.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 small bread loaf pans.

title: lorraine's scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel, slice and cook in salted water until soft, but still firm; drain.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Cream flour, margarine and sugar together. Press in bottom of 9x9x2 pan.
Bake 20 minutes. Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Pour over hot crust and bake 25 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into 2 inch squares.

title: seafood pasta
directions: Boil noodles until done
to your taste.
Rinse and trim fresh broccoli in small flowerets and cook with a small amount of water in covered casserole
in microwave about 3 minutes on High.
If using frozen,
follow directions on box.
In another bowl, melt butter and
garlic in microwave, covered, for about 2 minutes.
In large casserole,
combine noodles, broccoli and sealegs;
add garlic butter and layer cooper sharp cheese over top.
Cook, covered, in oven for about
hour
at
375° or until cheese is fully melted.

title: almond squares
directions: Mix the cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften the cream cheese.
Add 2 eggs and beat until smooth.
Add the confectioners sugar, vanilla and almond.
Mix well and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Remove and sprinkle the sliced almonds on top.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool thoroughly and cut in squares.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one step tamale pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onions and garlic until meat is browned and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients; toss lightly. Chill before serving.
If desired, garnish with toasted almonds.

title: chocolate chip brownies
directions: Cream together eggs, brown sugar and shortening.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 27 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool completely before cutting.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients; chill 1 hour before serving.

title: congealed tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and corn syrup.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat, adding vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour in greased dish.
Cut when cool.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oat pancakes(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat griddle over medium-high heat.
Oil lightly.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter on hot griddle.
Exchanges:
1 1/2 fat and 1/2 milk.

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until stiff. Gradually add sugar and vanilla.
Put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Heat oven to 425°.
Place meringue in oven and turn off heat. Leave in oven overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash till tender.
Mash squash, add other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim bread crusts.
Cook sausage in skillet, stirring until brown and crumbly; drain.
Layer 6 slices of bread, sausage, cheese and remaining bread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk and salt in bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour over layers.
Cover with foil and chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: easy baked perleau rice
directions: Brown rice in oleo.
Add beef soup and onion soup with 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook in casserole at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread dressing
directions: Cook together all ingredients except bread cubes; boil together 15 minutes.
Toss with fork into bread cubes.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in pan of water at 400°.
Serve with brown gravy.

title: mrs. fields cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in separate bowl, flour, ground oatmeal, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fresh spinach pasta toss
directions: Prepare Three-Step Homemade Pasta; set aside.
In a 4-quart Dutch oven, cook onion in butter over medium heat for 7 minutes or until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Add broth and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Stir in the pasta.
Top with spinach.
Cook, covered, for 1 to 2 minutes more or until spinach and pasta are tender.
To serve, ladle pasta into a bowl.
Top with cheese. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: supreme baked beans
directions: Saute onions and bacon (cut into smaller pieces).
Drain.
Add all ingredients including onions and bacon; mix.
If needed for a larger group, double this recipe.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and enjoy!

title: mommy's party crock-pot chicken wings
directions: In large container mix all ingredients together.
Marinate in refrigerator (covered) for 8 hours.
Pour into crock-pot, cook on high for at least 6 hours.

title: crunchy brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt and cocoa that has been sifted.
Put in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes. Remove and spread with 1 (7 ounce) jar of Marshmallow Creme.

title: corn souffle
directions: Let margarine come to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Butter baking dish.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a double boiler, melt almond bark.
Add can of Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Remove from heat.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into a buttered dish until set.
It will set fast!
Cut into squares and eat it all up!!

title: brunswick stew
directions: The vegetables may be fresh or canned.
Do not add salt to the cooked meats except for the chicken (1 1/2 teaspoons).
Mix everything together and simmer the afternoon or morning away. Enjoy!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook celery and onion in margarine or butter until tender.
Add water, chicken or turkey, carrots, bouillon, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf. Add noodles and parsley. Cook 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: In a small bowl, mix the yeast with the warm water. Dissolve completely. Add 1 tablespoon granulated sugar. Stir and set aside. In a large bowl, mix the flour, Crisco shortening and 1/4 cup granulated sugar. Add the milk and the yeast mixture. Mix well. Pour onto floured wax paper. Form into a ball. Coat the dough ball with melted margarine. Put into a plastic container with lid. The dough ball will rise so the container needs to be twice as big as the dough ball. Place in the refrigerator until ready to use. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all together and bake in pan for about 1 hour at 300°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 350° until firm.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Melt butter for the top of rolls when you bake them.
Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt and shortening.
Add flour and mix well.
Add softened yeast and eggs; beat well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto floured board and knead.
Place in greased bowl to let rise until double.
Make into rolls and let rise in greased baking pans. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt over double boiler the first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Remove from hot water.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into foil lined pans and chill.

title: fruit crunch cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer in this order: pineapple, pie filling, 1 cup pecans and dry cake mix.
Drizzle margarine over dry cake mix.
Sprinkle sugar and remaining nuts over top.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: jello salad
directions: One of the essential building blocks in any great cooking are stocks, used in soups, gumbos, sauce piquante, etc.
There is no substitute for a good stock and it is easy to make.

title: carol's wonderful biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour and nonfat dry milk until it has the consistency of cornmeal.
Add about 1/2 cup water and mix.
If the dough seems too thick, add a little more water and really stir strongly with a large spoon.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.
You can store uneaten biscuits in a Tupperware bowl in the refrigerator.
To reheat, you can wrap in a damp paper towel and microwave carefully (1 biscuit only for about 10 seconds) or place in a preheated oven for a few minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Fold in flour.
Add vanilla and salt, folding in gently.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: busy mom meat loaf(slow cooker)
directions: Place potatoes and carrots in slow cooker. Sprinkle with 1/4 teaspoon salt. Combine remaining ingredients. Mix well. Shape into a loaf. Place loaf on top of the vegetables, making sure it doesn't touch sides of slow cooker. Cover and cook for 8 to 10 hours on low.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cut length wise.
Scrape out meat of potatoes from peel.
Mash
potato meat with butter, cream, salt, onion, cheese, crab meat, and tabasco sauce.
Refill potato shells with mixture.
Bake at 425 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a medium skillet. Drain and discard any fat and set aside to cool. Lightly beat the eggs in a large mixing bowl. Add milk, mustard powder and salt and blend well. Stir in bread crusts, sausage and cheese and mix well. Pour into a shallow 2-quart glass baking dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut cream candy
directions: Put the sugar and milk of the coconut together in a saucepan. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add coconut and cook 10 more minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Pour into greased pans and cool.
Cut into squares.
Put in a cool place for 2 days to harden.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly; prick with a fork. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until tender. Allow potatoes to cool to touch. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact. Combine potato pulp and next 6 ingredients in a mixing bowl; beat until light and fluffy. Stuff shells with potato mixture. Combine Parmesan cheese and paprika; sprinkle over potatoes. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yield: 6 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients to make flavorful punch.
Serve over ice.

title: hearty chili
directions: Cook beans in 6 cups salted water for 1 to 2 hours or until tender.
Then drain and set aside.
Put onions, garlic, carrots, celery and green pepper in a saucepan with small amount of water. Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add bulghur, tomatoes, tomato paste, lemon juice and spices.
Combine with beans.
Heat gently in double boiler or in warm oven.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix chicken, vegetables, soup and cheese.
Place bottom crust into pie plate according to instructions.
Place chicken mixture on top of crust.
Cover with second crust.
Press crust edges together and trim excess.
Place several slits in top crust and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until crust is brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients; mix in oil.
Add all remaining ingredients; blend well.
Bake in greased floured pan at 325° for 45 minutes.
While cake is hot, cover with the following combination which has been brought to a boil:

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar, pumpkin and spices; set aside.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, Cool Whip and vanilla flavoring.
Spread most of mixture in bottom of pie crust.
Next place all of pumpkin on cream cheese mixture.
Use remaining cream cheese mixture to top pie.
Chill overnight.
Ready to serve.

title: virginia homestyle meat loaf
directions: Soak the bread in milk while you mix the other ingredients. Add the milk and bread mixture.
Place in a loaf pan and mix 1/2 cup catsup with four tablespoons of sugar and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for about one and a half hours.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place the carrots and onions in an ungreased 1 qt. baking dish; pour chicken broth over all. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until carrots are tender.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving the raisins until last. Put in greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, milk, salt and margarine.
Heat slowly. Bring to a boil and boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 25 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix soda and vinegar and set aside.
Mix cocoa, flour and dash of salt.
Mix alternately to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add last by hand, vinegar and soda mixture.
Bake at 350° in 2 greased and floured layer pans for 30 minutes.

title: the best one-dish meal
directions: Brown meat and onion in large saucepan.
Pour off excess fat. Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water.
Simmer until thick (10 to 15 minutes).
Pour meat mixture into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Strain juice from peas and pour over meat.
Pour prepared potatoes to fill up the rest of the pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese begins to brown (about 20 to 30 minutes).

title: pizza ritz
directions: Melt cheese.
Stir in sausage, soy sauce and salt.
Spoon onto bread.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and brown around edges.
Use hot sausage if you dare.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, celery, onion, water chestnuts, mayonnaise and cheese together; sprinkle with sugar and Tabasco.
Pour into 9 x 11 inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix melted margarine and crushed crackers together.
Sprinkle over casserole; bake 15 minutes more.
Flavors just need to blend together.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bierocks
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening.
Add cabbage.
Mix, cover and cook until cabbage is tender.
Roll out bread dough. Place 1/2 in casserole. Add meat mixture.
Sprinkle American cheese, diced up, over meat mixture.
Cover with remaining dough.
Seal edges and prick top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: savory stuffed meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Mix all ingredients except stuffing. Spread 2/3 of the mixture in ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches, pressing mixture up sides of pan to within 3/4-inches of the top. Spoon stuffing onto mixture in pan, then top with remaining meat mixture, covering stuffing completely.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Let stuffed meat loaf stand 5 minutes before cutting into thick slices.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar and let rest.
Add first mixture to second one and mix well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Let rise in bowl.
Punch down and shape in rolls or loaf.
Let rise again. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven; brush with butter.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix and cook cake mix as directed.
Make 4 layers or make 2 layers and split.
Mix softened cream cheese and blend in Cool Whip and sugars.
Spread mixture between each layer and top with blueberry pie filling, including top of cake.
Real good!

title: cream of asparagus soup with gruyere
directions: Blanch asparagus until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes.
Rinse under cold running water and drain.
Reserve 6 of the asparagus tips for garnish. Saute remaining asparagus in butter in a large saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Transfer to a food processor or blender and puree.
Mix puree and stock in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat to barely simmering.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Whisk together half and half, egg yolk and cheese in a small bowl. Whisk into soup.
Heat just until slightly thickened and soup is warm. Garnish with reserved asparagus tips. Season to taste.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: garden wedding punch
directions: *For brighter punch, use rainbow sherbet instead of lemon.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Stir constantly so it won't stick.
Take off heat, add vanilla and Rice Krispies, mix, let cool slightly.
Take a teaspoonful of mixture and make a ball. Butter hands to roll into a ball.
Then roll in coconut flakes.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Combine everything. Mix well. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with milk and margarine.
Take cake out of oven.
Pour caramel mixture over cake.
Add chips and nuts evenly over caramel mixture.
Pour rest of batter over this and bake an additional 20 minutes.
When cool, top with Cool Whip.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beating quick and making sure baking soda dissolves well.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, 3/4 cup milk and Crisco shortening.
Beat vigorously by hand or at medium speed with a mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, 1/2 cup milk and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: california baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Toss potato spears with dressing.
Sprinkle each spear with garlic powder and parsley.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes or until crispy.

title: metro's blueberry treat
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with water.
Add blueberry pie filling.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
Stir; let it get firm (best made day ahead).
Before serving, mix sour cream, soft cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts over all (if desired).

title: portia spiced tea
directions: Brew tea bags and boiling water for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: mattie's spaghetti salad
directions: Boil broken spaghetti until done.
Rinse real good with first hot and then cold water.
Mix cooked spaghetti, vegetables and salad dressing together.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff and set aside.
Mix baking powder with crackers.
Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks and milk mixture.
Add salt, nuts and crackers and beat until mixed.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: delia's elderberry pie
directions: Prepare crust for 2 crust pie.
Mix listed ingredients together.
Bake at 450° until crust is brown.
Reduce heat to 350° until it bubbles.
Turn off oven.

title: sweet n' sour spare ribs
directions: Put brown sugar and soy sauce in large electric skillet and cook until liquid.
Add juice from pineapple and dash garlic powder.
Add ribs and simmer until tender.
Add pineapple and enough cornstarch to thicken.

title: eva's guacamole dip ole
directions: In a large bowl, combine peeled avocados, garlic salt, red crushed peppers and onion powder.
Blend with potato masher until well
mashed and all avocado chunks are gone.
Add all other ingredients to avocado until well mixed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: quick cinnamon bread
directions: Mix egg, sugar and oil well.
Add soda and salt.
Mix well. Alternately add flour and buttermilk.
Beat well.
Place half of batter in greased loaf pan.
Sprinkle half of the cinnamon/sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat with remaining batter and sugar/cinnamon.
Cut through with knife and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: sheath cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, soda in a large mixing bowl.
Bring cocoa, oleo and water to rapid boil.
Add to flour mixture and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and pour in well-greased pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Icing must be ready to put on cake immediately after removal from oven.

title: cherry cinnamon cobbler
directions: Spread pie filling into a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Set aside icing from cinnamon rolls.
Arrange rolls around edge of baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cover and bake 10 minutes longer or until golden.
Spread icing over rolls.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pizza-potato hot dish
directions: Slice potatoes; brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Top with Mozzarella cheese, if desired, the last few minutes of baking.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press cracker crumbs in margarine.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in order listed in layers.
Pour condensed milk over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Toss chocolate and chopped nuts with 2 tablespoons of dry cake mix; set aside.
Beat remaining ingredients together for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Add soup and broth; warm.
Roll tortillas with chicken and cheese.
Pour soup mixture over them.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: pickle eggs
directions: Blend mustard with a little vinegar; add remaining vinegar Add next six ingredients; put on heat to simmer ten minutes, then take off.
Cool then pour over onion and eggs; put in a gallon jar.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in powdered sugar. Add cocoa and water to desired texture. Add vanilla and nuts.

title: banana pudding
directions: Add vanilla pudding, milk, sour cream and Cool Whip together. Layer bananas and vanilla wafers.
Spread filling between layers and on top.
Chill and serve.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, onion juice, mustard and salt in container of electric blender; blend well.
Slowly add oil, continuing to blend; blend until thick.
Add poppy seed; blend 2 minutes.
Chill.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Serve over fresh fruit.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: eggplant spaghetti
directions: In a large pot at medium high heat (no oil), cook onion, celery, eggplant and garlic clove, stir occasionally until onions are clear, then add tomatoes, brown sugar, parsley flakes and oregano.
Reduce heat to medium-low heat and cook about 30 to 40 minutes or until celery is tender.
Add the garlic powder and cooking wine and cook an additional 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti or noodles of your choice, cooked as directed.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Dribble melted oleo over graham cracker crumbs.
Mix and press down in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over crust.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil rice in milk until soft in top of double boiler; stir occasionally.
When rice is soft, remove from heat; add gelatin that has been dissolved in a little cold water.
Add sugar to rice when it is cooked.
Cool in pan of water.
Stir in egg, whip heavy cream and stir in when cool.
Add raisins, nuts and cherries.
Serves 8.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 3-quart baking dish.
Bring water and salt to boil.
Slowly stir in grits, cover and reduce heat; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese until melted; add egg, milk and sausage; blend well. Pour mixture in prepared dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake 1 hour or until cheese is browned.
Chill 10 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix nectar and juice from pineapple in a saucepan.
Heat just until boiling and pour over Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool to almost chill.

title: tater tot casserole no. 2(main dish)
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery.
When meat is done and veggies are tender, drain and then stir the soup into the mixture.
Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with frozen Tater Tots. Pour meat mixture over Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle on shredded cheese during the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to directions on back of package. Drain.
Mix the remaining ingredients together with the broccoli. Spoon into a lightly greased baking dish.
Crumble cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan(serves 6)
directions: Simmer chicken breasts in enough water to cover.
Add several pieces of chopped celery, a large onion (quartered).
Salt to season.
Cook for 1 hour.
Remove chicken pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package but take 2 minutes off cooking time.

Drain. Place broccoli spears in 13 x 9-inch pan or casserole (greased). Lay chicken pieces on top of broccoli, then mix soup, mayo, broth, lemon juice and curry powder together until smooth and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and add bread crumbs last with a little melted butter sprinkled over them.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven or until cheese is melted and heated through.

title: spinach salad
directions: Use a large refrigerator container with lid.
Layer spinach, onion, peas, cheese, mushrooms and bacon. Cover with a generous amount of mayonnaise and refrigerate overnight or several hours. Just before serving, toss well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat together the eggs, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla until blended.
Beat in dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake for about 40 minutes at 340°.
Cool on wire rack.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat until shortening and butter are melted.

title: creamy mexican party dip
directions: Soak your feet in a tub of warm water while you watch the news or read the paper.
Your feet contain many nerve endings and take a lot of abuse during the day.
They deserve an occasional treat.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In large bowl, mix soups with 1 soup can of broth. Add cheese, onions, green chilies and chicken. In oblong baking dish or pan, alternate layers of crushed chips with mixture beginning and ending with chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot relish
directions: Boil carrots, pepper and onion (carrots should be sliced crosswise) in salt and water just until tender.
Do not overcook. Mix the soup, sugar, oil, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook together.
Bring to a good boil for a minute or so. Pour over carrots, pepper and onion.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift salt, baking powder and flour two times.
Cream the sugar and butter.
Beat eggs into sugar and butter mixture, one at a time.
Alternate flour and sour cream approximately one at a time until all is combined.
Add the vanilla.
Pour batter into a tube pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine beef, water, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in large kettle.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove meat from soup; cut from bone in small pieces and return meat to soup.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes about 6 quarts.

title: tartar sauce
directions: This will keep several weeks if stored in a tight fitting container.

title: country style spareribs
directions: In bowl, combine beef broth, peach preserves, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and salt.
Place ribs in crock-pot.
Pour broth mixture over.
Place onion on top.
Cover and cook for 8 hours on low or 4 hours on high.
Remove ribs to platter.
Keep warm.
Measure 1 1/2 cups liquid; combine water and flour.
Blend into reserved liquid in saucepan.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Serve over ribs and noodles.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 13x9x2 inch baking pan with aluminum foil, extending ends of foil 1 inch over sides of pan. Grease and flour foil. Set aside. In medium saucepan, melt butter, stir in sugar and cocoa powder. Remove pan from heat, beat in eggs, one at a time, until blended. Stir in flour and vanilla until blended. Stir in 1 cup pecans. Pour into prepared pan, bake 25 minutes, until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars, then eggs, pumpkin and vanilla. Slowly add flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, then add oats and chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cherry bonbon cookies
directions: Drain cherries, reserving 1/4 cup juice for glaze; set aside. Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add 3/4 cup sugar, beating well.
Stir in flour and next 3 ingredients.
Shape into 24 balls.
Press each ball around a cherry, covering completely; place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and drizzle with cherry glaze.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: enchiladas
directions: In large pot, cook meat, half of the onions and all of the garlic until meat is done and onions are tender.
Drain grease off.
Add tomato paste, salt and chili powder.
Let simmer.
Place oil in skillet and heat.
Dip tortilla shells in hot oil until soft and drain on paper towels.
Spoon meat mixture into shells and roll up.
(This should use about half of meat mixture.)
Place in large baking dish or cookie sheets with deep sides.
Add second half of raw onions to leftover meat mixture.
Spoon over top of rolled meat/tortillas.
Cover tops with grated cheese and bake on 350° until cheese melts.
Makes 24 tortillas.

title: appetizer bacon snack
directions: Mash out slice of bacon and cut in 3 slices.
Wrap each tightly around a cracker, tucking ends underneath.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Makes a bow shaped snack.

title: grandma huffman's pickles
directions: Combine water, vinegar, salt, sugar and spices in a large pot. Bring to a boil.
Drop cucumbers in mixture and bring to a boil again.
Turn off heat.
Pack in jars.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: quick and easy chicken wings
directions: Clean and wash chicken wings.
Sprinkle underside of wing with a good coating of paprika.
Lay wing, back side up, in large frypan.
When wings are all in pan, sprinkle backs of wings with paprika (use lots).
Fill frypan 1/2-inch with water.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour or until wings are well done.
Turn wings on backs at half time.
Juice will thicken to make a nice sauce. Serve with rice.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Coat chicken pieces with flour.
In 12-inch skillet; heat oil, brown chicken on both sides.
Remove from heat.
In skillet, add mushrooms, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, tomato paste, water, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Return chicken to skillet; coat well with sauce.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer gently for 10 minutes or until chicken is tender, turning once.
Serves 6.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Bring sugar, syrup and butter to a boil; boil for one minute. Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Pour over cereal.
Press into a buttered 11 x 16-inch pan.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake according to directions on box.
Bake in 13 x 10-inch cookie sheet. Cool.

title: patrica's blonde brownies
directions: Mix well butter, flour, sugar and soda.
Beat in eggs.
Add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and add nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Arrange whole strawberries over baked pie shell.
Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and dash of salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir until thick and clear.
Add 1/4 cup strawberry Jell-O.
Mix well.
Cool and pour over pie.
Let set 4 hours in fridge before serving.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana bread(sugar free)
directions: Beat together mashed banana, oil and orange juice until creamy.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Beat well. Stir in nuts.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together the sugar, salt, vinegar and miracle whip.
Add pepper and onion.
Pour over cabbage and let stand 1/2 hour before serving.

title: oreo delight
directions: Take a 13 x 9-inch pan; pour 1 whole bag of Oreos in bottom of cake pan.
Crush until broken up.
Then sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar all over crushed areas.
Melt 1 stick butter; pour over Oreos all over also.
Then layer that with ice cream, by scooping ice cream out and layering over Oreos.
Finish up by layering with Cool Whip. Cover pan with foil or pan lid, if have; put in freezer and freeze up to 2 hours.
Then serve for when you have cravings.
You'll love it!!!

title: jarlsberg pasta primavera
directions: In large saucepan, cook vegetables in butter until just tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add flour.
Blend well.
Gradually add half and half.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Season with basil, salt and pepper.
Add cheese.
Cook, stirring, until melted.
Add broccoli.
Cook pasta according to directions on package; drain.
Toss with cheese mixture.
Serve immediately. Yields 4 main dish servings.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix molasses, water and baking soda.
Cool.
Mix flour, shortening, salt and brown sugar.
Reserve 1 cup of flour mixture for crumbs on top.
Mix the liquid with crumbs.
Sprinkle the cup of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese sauce
directions: In a pan, slowly heat the milk and cornstarch until thick. Add the cheese and seasoning salt, stirring until cheese is melted.
Serve over hot vegetables.

title: christmas logs
directions: Crumble vanilla wafers.
Mix everything together.
Roll into 2 logs.
Roll logs in sifted powdered sugar.
Roll in wax paper; refrigerate.
Slice as needed.

title: do-si-dos snickers bar cheesecake
directions: Chop cookies and butter fine in food processor.
Place in bottom of a spring-form pan 1/4-inch thick and refrigerate.

title: marinated beef salad
directions: Put the meat strips on a rimmed platter and cover with sliced onions.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Mix together the oil, vinegar, oregano, mustard, and salt.
Pour over the meat, cover and chill for at least 3 hours to mingle flavors.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
wax in microwave then add chocolate.
Keep chocolate hot and use tongs to dip balls.

title: skillet rice supper
directions: Brown frankfurters in oleo in a skillet.
Add rice, green beans, catsup and salt.
Simmer until heated through.
Sprinkle French fried onions on top before serving.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: If you are ambitious, you may make you own meatballs from the recipe.
But if you want to save time, you may use the meatballs found in the frozen food section of your grocery store.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon, and onion in skillet.
Drain. Combine all ingredients in a crock pot.
Heat on low for 4 hours.

title: onion biscuit topping
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add celery seed.
Cut shortening into mixture; blend in onions.
Add egg and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot Shanghai Casserole.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 27 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: sauce for wild duck
directions: Melt butter and jelly together over boiling water, blending well.
Just before serving, stir in lime juice, sherry and seasonings to taste and heat.
Makes 3/4 cup of sauce.

title: broccoli-rice cheese bake
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Mix undiluted soups, cheese, sauteed onion, celery and rice together for sauce.
Season to taste.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish and pour cheese-rice mixture over broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add milk and blend well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to creamed mixture, stirring only until all flour is moistened.
Spread half of batter in bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Spread 1/2 cup blueberries (fresh, frozen or canned) over batter and sprinkle on sugar and cinnamon mixture (2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon).
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine crumbs, margarine and 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: dill bread
directions: Heat cottage cheese, Crisco and sugar in small pan until warm. Stir in soda.
Add yeast and onion, softened in warm water.
Add egg last.
Add flour, a little at a time, until you have used 2 cups.
Leave the last 1/2 cup to knead the mixture for 5 minutes. Let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and put in greased loaf pan.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sugar and mustard.
Blend well.
Slowly add vinegar; blend.
Add celery seed, if desired, and milk; blend. Best if made the day before and put in refrigerator.
Add to slaw as needed.

title: orange chiffon cheesecake
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Blend crumbs and melted margarine together.
Press over bottom and halfway up sides of pan.
Bake for 8 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp fettucini alfredo
directions: Cook shrimp in 1/4 cup margarine. In large saucepan, combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk.
Stir over low heat until smooth. Add fettucini and shrimp.
Toss lightly.

title: breakfast shake(kids' recipe)
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: basic meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in ring-shaped pan and cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High power for 10 minutes, rotating at half time.
Let stand, still covered.
(Spread over top, if desired:
catsup, steak, barbecue or chili sauce.)

title: mac and cheese pizza hot dish
directions: Make 1 package of macaroni and cheese as directions say. Grease a cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
In a bowl, mix tomato sauce; add chopped onion, oregano, basil and pepper.
Pour over macaroni.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake another 10 minutes at 375°.

title: glorified chicken bake
directions: In 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange chicken, skin side up. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more until chicken is no longer pink and juice runs clear.
Stir sauce before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: port royal catfish stew
directions: Cook fish; save water.
Put celery, onion, potatoes and tomatoes in pan.
Add 2 pints of water, salt and pepper to taste. When ingredients are almost cooked, add fish.
(Makes about 2 quarts.)

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water for 5 minutes; cool.
Combine shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts to shortening mixture.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to raisin mixture and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Cook until done, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Bake at 400°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and let set 20 minutes.
Cream together brown and white sugars and shortening. Then add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry cake
directions: Line an 11 1/2 x 13-inch pan with 1/2-inch pieces of cake. Then put 1 1/2 cans cherries on cake.
Top with pudding mixed with 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 cup sour cream.
Put remaining cherries on top.
Let set 5 hours.

title: almond squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and salt.
Beat well.
Add almond extract.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with almonds and sugar.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss squash
directions: Melt oleo.
Add vegetables and cook until done.
Beat eggs and milk; add cheese and spices.
Pour vegetables in 13 x 9-inch pan. Pour egg mixture over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Add onion and mushrooms, if desired.)

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter & pour over dry mixture.
Add 2 well beaten eggs, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: easy cookie squares
directions: In
baking
dish prepare graham cracker crust by mixing graham crackers, butter and sugar.
Press in dish.
Spread 1/2 can sweetened
condensed
milk	over crust.
Spread chocolate chips and
peanut
butter chips over milk (may not require all of chips).
Spread coconut over chips.
Spread 1/2 can sweetened condensed milk over layers of chips and coconut.
Spread nuts over top
of
milk and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Let cool and cut into small squares.
Very rich.

title: sugar cookies
directions: To make sour milk, combine 3/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup vinegar. Combine sugar and butter to cream.
Add eggs and sour milk to creamed sugar and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Add enough flour so they roll nicely.
Chill at least one hour before rolling to cut.

title: tuna fish sauce with spaghetti
directions: Brown tuna fish,
garlic
and
parsley
in oil over low heat for 10
minutes.
Add
salt,
pepper, tomatoes and tomato puree; simmer 1 hour.
Add
oregano and basil; cook 5 minutes. Serve over spaghetti or
fine noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. This is a great quick meal during the Lenten season.

title: vanilla cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Boil margarine, vegetable oil and water. Pour over flour mixture and beat.
Stir in eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and soda mixture.
Pour into jelly-roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fresh asparagus with lemon sauce
directions: Break off asparagus stalks as far down as they snap easily. Cook covered in small amount boiling water till crisp and tender, 3-4 minutes, and drain.
Transfer asparagus to a warmed serving platter.
Melt butter and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to simmer, stirring occasionally.
Pour heated sauce over asparagus. Garnish with lemon slices.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Layer corn first in a greased dish.
Put beans on top of corn.
Mix sour cream, soup, onion and cheese.
Spread over corn and beans.
Mix margarine and crackers and spread on top. Sprinkle almonds on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pop up pie
directions: Dot the bottom of 2-quart casserole dish with oleo.
Mix sugar, flour and milk and stir.
Pour over dotted butter.
Add juicy fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes with skins on until tender.
Remove skins, slice into 2 to 3-inch thick slices and place in 9 x 13-inch dish. For syrup, combine Karo, sugar and oleo; bring to boil.
Pour over potatoes.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Bake covered in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, wine and 1 1/2 cups flour to which
salt,
cloves
and cinnamon have been added. Dredge cut up fruit
in
remaining
1 cup flour.
Fold dredged fruit and pecans
into
other
batter.
Batter will be very stiff. Drop by
teaspoons
on greased cookie sheet (make small).
Bake at 350° for
about
15 minutes or until slightly brown.
Makes many.
Store in airtight container.

title: rich lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar. Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and peanut butter until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and chill.
Some Cool Whip may be saved for topping, or add nuts or shaved chocolate, if desired.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Combine and freeze in your ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: appetizer wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs in thirds.
Empty beef into saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Bring liquid to boil.
Add hot dogs.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes. Put into crock-pot to simmer.

title: chewey pralines
directions: In a heavy 4-cup saucepan, heat butter, sugar, syrup, milk and salt. Bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly with wooden spoon until candy thermometer reads 250°. Remove from heat and add vanilla and pecans. Cool a few minutes and place by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Let sit overnight.

title: pizza
directions: Mix flour and water.
Add tomato sauce.
Put on cheese and pepperoni.
Cook at 200° for 5 hours.

title: chili con carne
directions: Brown the beef and onion in the butter (or bacon drippings). Add the beans and tomato soup and cook for 10 minutes.
Add chili powder, flour, water and salt which has been mixed into a paste. Cook slowly for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: layered hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Put in casserole (first layer), then layer other ingredients.
Add water.
Cook on top of stove for 1 hour.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened, about 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Add coconut and nuts. Stir by hand until thick enough to spread.

title: creamy tuna pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta salad as directed on package, adding remaining ingredients with spice pack.
Chill.
Stir in bacon bits just before serving.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Mix potatoes and oil in 9-inch pie plate.
Press into pie crust shape.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes until crust begins to brown.
Remove from oven.
Layer on cheese, meat and onion; set aside.
Combine milk, eggs and seasoning in bowl, beat until blended.
Pour egg mixture over layered ingredients.
Return to oven; bake for 30 minutes or until light brown.
Allow to cool 5 minutes before cutting into wedges.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and pecans in 2-quart batter bowl, using the spoon. In small bowl, combine melted butter and eggs. Mix the butter and egg mixture with dry ingredients until flour is just moistened. Fill the individual cups of the nonstick mini muffin pan 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and grits casserole
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil; stir in grits.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cool Whip with mixer.
When smooth, fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Keep in freezer until 10 minutes before serving.

title: breakfast coffee cake
directions: Piece together one can of rolls so no holes remain and lay into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish to fit.
In bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar, the yolk of egg only, lemon juice and vanilla. Pour all over the one can of rolls (don't put to edge).
Piece together the second can of rolls and put over the cream cheese mixture in dish.
Brush top with beaten egg white.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or lightly brown.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
May be refrigerated the night before and brought back to room temperature to serve.

title: 30 minute apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and vinegar.
Boil hard for 20 minutes; stir constantly.
Add candy and boil 10 more minutes.
Stir often. Pour in jars and seal.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes. Makes 5 pints.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, put pumpkin, 1/2 of Cool Whip, pudding mix and spice.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Pour into crust. Top with remainder of Cool Whip and chill.
Makes 6 servings. Equals 3/4 vegetable, 3/4 bread and 92 optional.

title: ho-ho cake
directions: In saucepan, cook together flour and milk until thick and smooth.
Chill until thoroughly cooled.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and taco seasoning mix according to directions on package.
Break lettuce into pieces in large bowl. Add other ingredients and toss.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple and milk. Set in refrigerator overnight. Add lemon juice, food coloring (a few drops), Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate before serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: The last 4 ingredients may be doubled.

title: key lime pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks. Gradually beat in sugar, 1 tbsp at a time. Beat 4 minutes longer until stiff, glossy peaks form and sugar is dissolved.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop or shred pepper and carrot.
Place in a bowl or pan that will be big enough to toss after liquid is added. Put ingredients in medium saucepan.
Heat, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves; bring to a slight boil.
Remove from heat and pour over cabbage mixture and toss until cabbage shrinks. Place in refrigerator, covered.
After it cools, put in freezer bags and put in the freezer.
When ready to use, thaw out and put remaining in the refrigerator.

title: fresh apple bake
directions: Mix soda, salt and flour.
Then add eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix apples and pecans last.
This batter will be thick.
Spread in a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla and nuts.
Cook very slowly, stirring frequently, it sticks easily, until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Cool 15 minutes.
Beat and add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 8x8 or 9x9 lightly buttered pan.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix onions, mayonnaise, Swiss cheese and Tabasco.
Spread mixture into a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese evenly over mixture and sprinkle with paprika to taste.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve warm as a dip with your favorite chips or crackers.
Yields 16 servings.

title: beef and brew
directions: In a large saucepan, stir together beer, 3/4 cup water, bay leaf, 1/2 teaspoon salt, thyme and ground pepper.
Stir in meat. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 55 minutes. Add onions and peppers; simmer about 20 minutes or until beef is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter and oil in skillet over high heat.
Add onions, garlic and lemon juice.
Stir until onions are soft.
Add shrimp and stir until pink, approximately 3 minutes.
Stir in lemon zest, parsley and Tabasco.
Serve over rice.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: strawberry yogurt shake
directions: Add ingredients, in order listed, to blender container.
Puree at medium speed, until thick and smooth.
Makes two (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper. Place in 9 x
13-inch
dish.
Melt oleo and mix with crackers. Spread on top
of
vegetable	mixture.
Bake	at
for 45 minutes. Yields:
8 to 10 servings.

title: hamburger loaf
directions: Brown beef and add soup.
Place in casserole dish and pour peas on top.
Layer mashed potatoes over top.
Heat in 350° oven until bubbly around edges.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bone cooked chicken.
In large pan, melt butter.
In bowl, mix cut up chicken with chipped up boiled eggs.
Place this mixture in pan.
Pour mixture of mushroom soup and broth over it.
In bowl, mix milk, flour and shortening.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Cook in 350° oven until brown.

title: white chili
directions: 1. Cook onions in water until soft and clear.

title: mexicana layered dip
directions: Mix beans, cheese, 4 tablespoons of onions and seasonings in saucepan and heat on low, stirring occasionally until cheese melts. Pour into a 9 x 13 glass dish. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Top with sour cream, tomatoes and remaining onions. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salsa
directions: Melt cheese in microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Add salsa and chilies.
Mix well.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: ham-agetti casserole(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, microwave (covered) bacon on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove approximately 1/2 the fat.
Add ham, tomatoes, spaghetti, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper. Stir well.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 18 to 20 minutes or until spaghetti is tender.
Stir after 8 minutes and once more before cooking is finished.
Finally sprinkle with shredded cheese and microwave on High, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes until cheese melts. Makes 6 servings.
Great for leftover Christmas or Easter ham!

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain juice from shrimp, save.
Mix all ingredients in electric mixer, add a bit of juice if needed.
Serve with favorite cracker.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in vanilla, flour and nuts. Makes very stiff dough.
Use a drop of milk, if needed.
Chill. Shape in small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: clam fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and pepper.
Combine beaten eggs, clams and milk mixture (milk and clam juice).
Add to flour mixture to make thick batter.
Deep fry at 360° until golden brown.
Serves a gang.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together; except the rolled oats. Dissolve the soda in sour cream.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam; place sliced potatoes and onion in layers.
Place pork chops on top; cover and bake at 350-375° for 30 minutes; turn pork chops over and continue baking for 30 minutes (til chops are done);
uncover the last 15 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: In large mixing bowl, place nuts, chocolate chips, chocolate bar (broken in small pieces), marshmallow cream and vanilla. In a saucepan, place sugar and Pet milk.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over contents in bowl.
Stir until melted.
Then pour into buttered pan.
When set, cut into squares.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Add potatoes, eggs, syrup, spices, salt, butter and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: healthy champagne delight
directions: Combine pieces of fruit in a bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent darkening.
Sparsely sprinkle the sugar over the fruit and stir.
Chill.
When ready to serve, divide fruit in 4 sherbet glasses.
Pour chilled pink champagne over fruit.

title: neiman marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs, butter, and nuts.
Press into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Next mix cream cheese, sugar, 2 eggs, and vanilla.
Spread on top of chocolate layer.
Bake 35 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cake will look soft when taken out of oven.
Cool completely.
Spread cool whip, coconut, and nuts over cake and finish with Hershey bar shaved on top.
Best if sets for 24 hours.

title: summer garden fish
directions: Wash, then pat dry flounder.
Melt butter over flounder.
Mix together diced tomato, celery, onion, green pepper and mushrooms. Place fish on double layered aluminum foil and pour vegetables over fish.
Add spices and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or grill on a barbecue until fish is done.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Add other ingredients.
Cook on medium-high heat until potatoes are soft.
Good served over rice.

title: egg salad with chives
directions: Combine eggs, celery, carrots, mayonnaise, chives and seasoned salt; mix until blended.
Cut tomatoes in 6 sections almost to stem end; fill each with approximately 1/3 cup egg salad.
Garnish with carrots and chives, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.
May use salad as a spread for a sandwich.

title: laredo supper
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add onion and pepper. Cook until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes. Serve warm with corn chips, if desired.

title: fantasy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Drop big tablespoons of batter onto cookie sheet (I use a No. 40 ice cream scoop).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove seeds and membranes.
Arrange in a deep round casserole dish.
Mix together raw beef, cooked rice, onions, salt and pepper.
Before you stuff the peppers, mix soup with 1/2 cup water.
Add 1/2 cup of soup mixture with combined items.
Mix together well and stuff peppers; cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 28 to 30 minutes, turning 1/4 turn every 7 minutes.
Grate cheese; sprinkle over tops when cooked.
Let stand long enough to melt cheese.

title: peanut pleasin pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar until crumbly.
Reserve 1/4 cup to sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter mixture into baked pie shell.

title: witch's brew
directions: Pour cranberry juice in a large bowl.
Add apple cider.
Stir in orange juice.
Mix well; serve heated or cold.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks after it is well creamed.
Add extract, then flour gradually to creamed mixture. If not
soft
enough to come out of cookie press, add a little milk. Bake in 325° oven for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer vegetables as listed.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar. Spread over top layer.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bacon bits. Salad should be prepared several hours before serving.
Place, covered, in refrigerator.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and let stand for 1 hour. Drain, rinse well with cold water and drain well.
To this mixture, add the next 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pack in jars and seal.
A very good sweet relish to use on hot dogs or sandwiches.

title: green bean and swiss cheese casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and saut lightly. Mix beans and cheese and pour into an 8 x 10 buttered casserole. Pour hot sour cream mixture over beans. Top with the Pepperidge Farm stuffing crumbs that have been rolled in 6 tablespoons butter.

title: nancy's real good pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and butter and mix.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: old west chili
directions: In skillet combine the first 6 ingredients over medium heat. In large kettle combine the rest of the ingredients and boil. Reduce heat to a simmer and add skillet mixture.
Then add 1 large can tomato sauce.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown pork, add onions and brown. Add remaining ingredients, cook 10 minutes on top of stove, stirring occasionally. Then place in a casserole and bake 1 hour in a 350 degree oven. Serves: 6.

title: anadama bread
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil and stir in cornmeal.
Stir in and cool to lukewarm the molasses and shortening.
Mix dough then knead.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down.
Turn into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until dark brown.
Makes two loaves, the recipe doubles well.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix together and let set for 2 hours the cabbage, sweet pepper, carrot and salt.
Mix together and cook the sugar, vinegar, water and celery seed and mustard seed; pour over cabbage mixture while hot.

title: chicken curry - in a hurry
directions: In a large skillet, saute chicken, mushrooms and onion in oil until chicken is lightly browned on all sides.
Stir in flour, broth and curry powder.
Add apple and parsley, then pour in milk and water.
Simmer, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes, or until apple pieces are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Saute garlic, onion and ground beef.
Add celery and carrots; simmer.
Add next 6 ingredients and water.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add frozen veggies.
Simmer until tender.
Cook orzo according to package directions.
Add to soup.
Add parsley.
Serve with Romano.

title: harold's favorite red potato salad
directions: Cover potatoes with lightly salted water and add lemon juice. Bring rapidly to a boil; turn heat down to just a rolling boil. Cook potatoes until tender when pierced with the point of a knife, about 12 minutes or more.
Drain and cool.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix and chill overnight (or couple of hours).
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake or do not press down.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in chopped pecans.

title: potato bread
directions: Combine in order given, following directions for bread making.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order listed; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal, sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in melted butter, then add egg and vanilla.
Line cookie sheet with parchment paper.
Drop batter by teaspoon, 2 inches apart. Flatten cookies with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 5 minutes.
Cool on parchment paper.
Makes 35 cookies.

title: boss' mexican chicken
directions: Bake chicken and remove from bone.
Place chicken pieces in large baking dish.
Mix together soups, onion, pepper, Ro-Tel, green chilies and seasonings.
Place a layer of frozen flour tortillas over chicken pieces, then add a layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Next, add the sauce mixture.
Finally, top with another layer of grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: Mix
graham
cracker
crumbs,
dates,
marshmallows and pecans together.
Add Eagle Brand milk to mix.
Sprinkle small part of reserved graham cracker crumbs on foil.
Roll mixture in crumbs and
chill for 2 hours, then cut into slices.
Makes 4 rolls.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cream together cottage cheese, mayonnaise and cream cheese. Mix all ingredients together except Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in 9 x 9 square pan or large round chafing dish.
Serve hot with assorted crackers or bagel chips.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour apples in an 8-inch square pan. Combine the remaining ingredients; mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until apples are tender.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Chill if desired. Great for picnics.

title: cheeseburger quiche
