directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain well.
Beat together eggs, mayonnaise and milk.
Add 1 cup cheese and seasoning; beat well. Add hamburger mix.
Pour into shell; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rosie's ricotta pizza pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shape your own pizza dough into 12-inch circle.
Thinly spread a simple tomato sauce evenly on top.
In a medium size bowl, mix together the Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese and milk.
Apply this evenly over sauce; it will be lumpy.
Sprinkle over and around Ricotta mixture the following:
tomatoes, basil, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook for approximately 25 minutes on rack in center of oven.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Beat peanut butter and margarine at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls and chill 10 minutes or until firm.
Microwave chocolate and shortening at high setting for 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Dip each peanut butter ball in melted chocolate mixture until partially coated.
Place on wax paper to harden.
Yield:
7 dozen.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix Veg-All, soup, garlic salt, black pepper, lemon juice, beaten egg and mayonnaise.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers, then cheese on top.
Cook about 1/2 hour.

title: lemon sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet, one tablespoon at a time, so it melts as it is added.
Add the pineapple and juice. Chill until slightly set. Fold in the cottage cheese and pour mixture into a mold. Let set.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Pat dry with paper towels.
In skillet, cook chicken in oil for 10 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Drain off fat.
Pour salsa over chicken in skillet.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes until tender when pierced with a fork. Transfer chicken and salsa to a platter.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serve with the tortilla chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potato praline pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Combine the eggs, sweet potatoes, sugar, brown sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake for about 40 minutes or until set.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 370° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(Can freeze.)
These cookies stay nice and moist.

title: vegetable parmesan casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and mix.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and mix well.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: norma's cream of broccoli
directions: Cook until tender the first 6 ingredients for 20 to 30 minutes.
Mix half and half and flour into paste; add Cheez Whiz. Simmer (do not boil).
Add to vegetables.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Crust:
Combine ground nuts, cracker crumbs, margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Press onto bottom and about 1 1/2 inches up side of 9-inch greased pan.
Set aside.

title: burrito pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Flatten crescent rolls in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine hamburger, sauce, seasoning and beans; spread over rolls.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Arrange pecans in bottom of pie shell.
In mixing bowl beat eggs, add butter, Karo and vanilla; mix until well blended. Combine sugar and flour and blend with egg mixture.
Pour over nuts.
Let stand until nuts rise to surface.
Bake 350° 40-45 minutes.

title: raspberry mango refresher
directions: In a blender, combine and liquify the mango, raspberries, mint, ice, water and sugar.
Pour into 2 or 3 wine glasses. Layer the whipped cream on top.
Top with raspberries and a mint leaf.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Mix egg, vinegar and water to make 1 cup of liquid.
Mix this well with first mixture.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Fry hamburger meat until brown; brown sliced onion in oleo or butter.
Pour hamburger, onion, carrots, potatoes, tomatoes and green beans into a large pot.
(Carrots and potatoes may be cut into very large pieces if desired.) Add salt and pepper to taste. Add the water.
Simmer for approximately an hour or more.
Serves approximately 5 to 6 people.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Melt butter; saute onion and green pepper.
Add flour, salt, mustard and red pepper.
Stir in milk.
Cook until boiling and thickened.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Drain mushrooms and hominy and stir until well mixed.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add
sour
milk,
soda,
eggs, bananas, vanilla, flour and salt.
Put in
x 11-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake at 350° until browned well.
Frost when cool and cut in bars.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, saute beef and onion.
Add salt, pepper, bell pepper, seasoning mix, tomatoes, tomato sauce, beans, marjoram and bay leaf.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Top with corn chips.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix ingredients together, except shells.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup stewed tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and dates until thick
(about 10 minute). Cool.
Add Rice Krispies and nuts and roll into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: butter crunch bars
directions: Melt butter over low heat in 2-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Stir until well blended.
Return to cook on low heat.
Continue to stir until mixture reaches full rolling boil. Add water and syrup; mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Heat to 390° or soft crack stage.
Remove from heat, stir in 3/4 cup nuts immediately.
Pour into lightly greased (buttered) 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread with spatula.
Let cool. Remove from pan.
Place on wax paper.
Melt and spread chocolate on top.
Let stand until chocolate is set.
Break into pieces.

title: venus demilo soup
directions: Fry hamburger and drain well.
Put all ingredients in pan except pasta.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Add pasta and cook 15 minutes more.
Serve with salad and crusty bread.

title: grape nut pudding
directions: Pour Grape-Nuts into scalded milk and allow to stand in warm place for 10 minutes.
Beat eggs and sugar together; stir into cooled Grape-Nuts.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir several times while baking.

title: italian macaroni with bacon
directions: Fry the shredded bacon until crisp.
Cook onions with bacon until brown (do not drain grease).
Add cooked macaroni, tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg, oil and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° until toothpick placed in center comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients, except bread.
Serve on bread or in a pita bread.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: home care gingerbread houses
directions: Bring butter or shortening, sugar, molasses and vinegar to a boil.
Cool, add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture; mix well.
Chill.
On lightly floured surface, roll out to about 1/8 inch thickness for thin cookies or 1/4 inch for plump cookies.
Cut in disired shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375 F for 6-12 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from sheet.

title: roquefort dip
directions: Mix all but Roquefort in bowl with mixer.
Add Roquefort, but blend just enough to mix in (unless you want it smoother).

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms; remove stems.
Chop stems finely.
In large skillet, melt butter; add onions, celery and mushroom stems. Simmer until celery is tender.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Fill mushroom caps with onion mixture.
Arrange caps, stuffed side up, in the same skillet.
Simmer for 5 minutes, covered.
Serve with steaks, chops or chicken, etc.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2/3 cup water.
In mixer bowl, put cake mix, dissolved Jell-O, 2 eggs at a time (beat), then other 2 eggs and 2/3 cup oil.
When mixed, bake in preheated oven. I use temperature on box.
Use greased and floured tube pan.

title: summer tea
directions: Steep water and tea bags for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add enough cold water to make 1 gallon.
Stir well. Serve over ice with mint or small slice of orange.

title: pot roast of beef
directions: Flour and brown to make a sauce to roast beef in:
Add all ingredients except carrots, potatoes and cornstarch.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
The last hour add carrots and potatoes.
Bake until done.
Thicken with cornstarch and water to your taste.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients. Mix well.
Refrigerate.
Form into small balls; roll into Sugar Mixture.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Put oil in bottom of pan with onion, hamburg, salt and pepper. After hamburg is cooked, add remainder of ingredients and boil for 3 hours with cover halfway on.

title: lemon pudding fruit
directions: Drain fruit.
Save pineapple juice.
Pour pineapple juice over sliced bananas and let sit for 1 hour.
(This keeps bananas from turning brown.)
Add fruit and sprinkle pudding mix over fruit.
Mix slightly.
Cover and keep refrigerated.

title: jambalaya
directions: Mix above ingredients and cook according to box directions. Enjoy!

title: cole slaw dressing(makes 1-quart)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Refrigerate and use as needed.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, beans and 2/3 c. of the French-fried onions in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir.
Sprinkle with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, onion and bacon together in a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over salad.
Mix well.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt oleo in pie pan you cook in. Mix all other ingredients and pour over oleo. Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Whipping cream, butter and eggs should be at room temperature. Add butter and sugar, adding sugar a little at a time.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour and whipping cream.
Add vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt cake pan at 300° for 1 3/4 hours or until tests done.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350° and let cool.
Beat cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar and 1/2 of carton Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding with 2 1/2 cups of cold milk.
Beat 2 minutes and spread on cream cheese mixture.
When set, spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Chopped nuts may also be added.

title: chicken-rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, butter and onion until tender-crisp.
Add soup and mix well.
Add rice and chicken and mix well.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Pour
boiling
water over 1 cup All-Bran and let stand. Mix together the sugar, shortening, eggs and buttermilk.
Add the flour,
baking soda, salt and the rest of the All-Bran to the All-Bran
mixture.
Combine
both mixtures and put in the refrigerator.
Stir
and
put
in
muffin
pans.
Bake
for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: quick and easy nutty cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Stir together in a medium bowl until well mixed, dry cake mix, melted butter or margarine and 3/4 cups chopped nuts.
Press in pan.
Top with topping.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Spoon into muffin pan and bake at 450° until done (approximately 10 to 15 minutes). Place remaining batter in refrigerator to use as needed.
Too easy to believe rolls!

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cornflakes, butter and almonds in a greased casserole.
Top with those and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: the digestive cocktail
directions: Squeeze juice from all citrus juices.
Mix well and serve.

title: mom's approval sandwich
directions: Spread margarine on bread.
Add corned beef.
Top with Parmesan and honey to taste.
Microwave about 1 minute.

title: celebration punch
directions: Mix ingredients in a 5-quart container.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 5 hours before using.
Add 2 quarts of 7-Up before serving. Makes 40 (5 ounce) servings.

title: corn flakes treats
directions: Mix sugar and white syrup in a 3-quart saucepan.
Measure peanut butter and corn flakes separately and set aside.
Cook sugar and syrup on medium heat just until it comes to a good boil. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add corn flakes and mix well until they are coated good.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cook minced onion in oil until yellowed.
Add meat; cook until browned.
Add parsley, carrot and seasonings; cook 5 minutes.
Cut bread into 3 equal parts.
Pull out soft center of loaf; mix with meat.
Add grated onion and water.
Mix all together very well. Stuff into bread; pack in very tightly.
Put loaf into foil; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix together, adding pineapple juice last.
Pour into mold and chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: the milazzo's monster nachos
directions: Cover entire plate with nachos.
Cover nachos with cheese, then beans.
Add another layer of nachos, then cheese.
Top with black olives and scallions.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes. Top with sour cream.
Enjoy!
Yummy!

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: In a large bowl sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
In a small bowl beat together egg and milk.
Stir milk and egg into flour mixture.
Mix in the butter and fold in the blueberries.
Set aside for 1 hour.

title: chiffon cake(granddaughter's favorite)
directions: Sift flour, then measure.
Add sugar and mix together in bowl. Make a well and add in order:
oil, egg yolk, water, vanilla and rind.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Measure egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl.
Beat until whites form a very stiff peak.
Pour egg yolk mixture into beaten whites, gently folding with wooden spoon just until blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.
Invert on funnel.
Let hang until cold.
Serve plain or frost with White Mountain Frosting.

title: peanut gingerbread bars
directions: Whisk water and peanut butter.
Add gingerbread mix and stir. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salt water for 10 minutes.
Drain. Put in baking dish.
Blend soup, cheese and milk.
Heat until cheese melts.
Pour over cabbage.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until heated.

title: barbecued hamburgers
directions: Combine vinegar, catsup, allspice, mustard, chili powder, water, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add browned meat.
Toast buns. Pour mixture over toasted halves.
Add pickle and sliced onion to each half.
Serve immediately.

title: hidden valley stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add chicken, stir in dressing mix. Stir to coat chicken.
Add thawed vegetables and water. Stir-fry about 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Blend all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add all liquid ingredients next.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: May use any kind of cream soup.
Mix green beans, soup, dry soup and cheese; sprinkle with salt, pepper and onion salt.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 50 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir pumpkin and sugar together and heat until hot. Add the milk and molasses heated, then combine the balance of the ingredients. Pour into an unbaked crust. Preheat oven and bake at 425° for twenty minutes, then reset the temperature and bake twenty minutes longer at 325°.

title: punch
directions: Mix above ingredients and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Combine other ingredients and add to cooked and drained broccoli.
Bake in buttered casserole dish 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grilled steak italian
directions: Combine Italian dressing, mustard and pepper. Place steaks on grill to cook slowly.
Brush frequently with sauce, turning every 10 to 15 minutes.
Continue cooking, brushing with sauce to keep moist.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Cook chicken breasts.
Remove bones and cut up; set aside. In oil, cook onions (cut in 1/4-inch slices) and garlic.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in chicken.
Combine tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, oregano, pepper, celery seed or flakes and bay leaves.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes longer.
Stir occasionally. Remove bay leaves.
Skim off excess fat.
Serve over noodles or spaghetti.

title: calico salad
directions: Cook vegetables in salted boiling water 8 minutes.
Drain well.
Add all other ingredients and chill.

title: lois' raspberry biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Separate biscuits and cut each one in half horizontally.
Dip each half in melted butter on both sides and then in cinnamon-sugar mix.
Place half a biscuit in lightly greased muffin cups or on a cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon preserves in the center of each and cover with other biscuit half.

title: brown rice
directions: Wash rice and combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.

title: swedish pie
directions: Cream butter and 1/2 C. sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Makes a stiff batter.
Divide batter into 2 well-greased pie tins.
Place 1 C. apple sauce over each layer. Beat egg whites until stiff gradually adding 1 C. sugar.
Place on top of apple sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 325 degrees.
Remove from oven and serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook milk and sugar together until forms a soft ball.
I use a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add:
1 cup peanut butter and 1- 7 oz jar marshmallow fluff.
Blend well and stir until it hold its shape.
This happens fast.
Have your pan prepared before hand by greasing with butter and be ready to pour fudge in it to set up.

title: olive sandwich spread
directions: In a small bowl, mix all ingredients.
Spread on crackers. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fudge pillows
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut margarine into flour and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, and vanilla, tossing with fork until all flour is moistened and dough cleans side of bowl.
Divide dough into halves. Roll each half into rectangle, 12 x 8-inches, on cloth-covered board generously sprinkled with sugar.
Cut each lengthwise into four 2-inch strips.
Prepare Fudge-Cream Cheese Filling.
Drop filling by rounded teaspoonfuls into 6 mounds, 1 inch apart, onto 1 strip; top with another strip.
Cut into six 2-inch squares; seal edges securely.
Place squares about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining strips and filling.
Bake until light golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: baked spaghetti supper
directions: Cook spaghetti using package directions; drain.
Mix half the soup mix, 1 tablespoon flour and sour cream in bowl.
Stir into spaghetti.
Spoon into 2-quart buttered casserole, making well in center.
Brown ground beef in butter in skillet, stirring occasionally; remove from heat.
Add 1/4 cup flour, dry milk powder, salt, pepper and remaining soup mix; mix well.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Spoon onto center of spaghetti.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: yellow squasherole
directions: Microwave butter at High 1/2 to 1 minute; add cracker crumbs and pecans; microwave at High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Set aside.
In 1-quart casserole, place water, salt and squash. Cover.
Microwave at High, 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes until tender.
Drain.
Mix together mayonnaise, egg, cheese, melted butter, sugar and onion.
Pour over squash, mixing well.
Microwave at Medium 4 minutes.
Stir, then add crumb topping.
Microwave at Medium, 2 to 4 minutes more until center is set.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: funny cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in pie shells.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7 up and cornstarch until clear, stirring constantly until thick. Add jello, cool. Add 8 to 10 pkg of equal to suit your taste. Add strawberries and pour into pie crust. Refrigerate. Serves 8.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix four ingredients well and chill covered for several hours or overnight.

title: walking taco chip dip
directions: For bottom layer, spread refried beans over plate.

title: seafood stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add Crab Delights and vegetables and stir over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.
Cook 1 minute more.
Garnish with chow mein noodles.

title: apple pie
directions: Place crust in pie pan; set aside.
Place apples, sugar and margarine in skillet.
Heat until margarine melts, stirring to coat apples.
Sprinkle on spice and stir.
Dump in crust; cover with top crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes, or until top is golden and apples are bubbly.

title: baked game hens
directions: Put rice in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Top with game hens.
Add water and spices from rice package.
Add celery, green onions, water chestnuts, mushrooms and wine.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chilled angel delight
directions: Break up cake and fill bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Soften candy bars in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add 4 egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into Milky Way mixture.
Beat whipping cream until very stiff. Add Milky Way mixture to whipped cream.
Pour over angel food cake.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Chill or freeze.
Serve either chilled or frozen.
Delicious served frozen.

title: cinnamon brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup, water, salt and food coloring in pan.
Stir only to dissolve.
Cook to 300°. Remove from heat.
Add butter, vinegar and oil of cinnamon.
Stir as little as possible. Pour into 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased pans.
Let cool and break into small pieces.

title: logan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Turn into a greased roasting pan. Bake one hour. Cut into squares. Allow to air-dry until squares are semi-dry. Yield: Enough to sustain two men 16 days.

title: sucker salmon
directions: Scale and clean fish; dry well.
Use pint jars.
Cut fish in 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Place with fish skin side to jar.
In each pint jar, put 1 tablespoon vinegar, 1 tablespoon catsup, 1 tablespoon Wesson oil and 1 teaspoon canning salt.
Pressure can 90 minutes at 10 pound pressure.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Mix well, bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch buttered pan.
Let cool and ice with chocolate ready-made frosting.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add salt, garlic powder, catsup and sour cream; mix well.
Separate dough into 20 biscuits.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll each biscuit to a 4 x 4-inch square.
Place approximately 1/4 cup meat mixture on center of each square.
Fold over corner of square to form a triangle; seal edges with fork.
Cut 3 (1/2-inch) slits on top.
Bake until golden brown at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Brush with melted butter, if desired.

title: jerk chicken wings
directions: Rub seasoning on wings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, basting thoroughly.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix and put in ham slices. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° glass dish). In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over margarine, pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients, press down firmly.
Bake until light brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars after cooled thoroughly.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix all and refrigerate until serving.

title: orange glazed chicken(diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup mix and orange concentrate.
Place chicken in shallow pan and brush with half soup/orange mixture.
Bake 1 hour, basting frequently or until chicken is tender.

title: coconut fruit bowl
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in sour cream and salt. Chill overnight.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Add soda to applesauce and beat until puffy.
Warm applesauce mixture.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add to applesauce and beat until creamy.
Add spices. Stir in flour.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 cake.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2-quart casserole.

title: swedish coffee braid
directions: Sprinkle dry yeast into warm water.
Combine milk, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt; stir until butter is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Cool mixture until warm.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Add softened yeast, egg yolk and 1 teaspoon cardamom; beat hard.
Stir in 3 cups flour (remaining flour is used as necessary for kneading dough).
Turn dough out on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (8 to 10 minutes).
Shape into ball; place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.

title: little pizza appetizers
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on rye bread.
Broil at 550° 5 inches from flame for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: lit'l smokies sausage rolls
directions: Roll biscuits into round patties.
Place Lit'l cheddy sausage inside biscuit and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes great party treats.
Serve with Lit'l Smokies German Dipping Sauce.

title: butternut squash pie
directions: Boil the butternut squash until soft, then mash while hot. Add butter, flour and sugar.
Mix eggs with some of the hot ingredients, then add to all of mixture.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and dice eggplant.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes.

title: superior french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a quart jar and shake vigorously. A garlic may be placed in the dressing overnight for added flavor.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together and store in dry place.
Use 1/3 cup mix for each cup boiling water.

title: stuffed mirliton
directions: Boil mirlitons until tender.
Scrape from shell when cool, reserving shells.
Remove large seed.
In large iron skillet, place butter, seasonings, shrimp (cleaned) and mirliton pulp.
Mix well and let cook until tender and well blended.
Add 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Blend well.
Stuff into shells and top with bread crumbs and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies; cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork; pour Kahlua over brownies and set aside.
Make Jell-O pudding with 4 cups whole milk.
Break candy bars in small pieces; crumble half the soaked brownies and place in a glass dish or bowl.
Cover with half the pudding, then half the candy and half the Cool Whip (in layers).
Repeat layers (save some candy for topping). Refrigerate.
Very rich and gooey.

title: best ever nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Add baby food. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: never fail divinity
directions: Mix sugar, water, syrup and salt together.
Cook rapidly to soft ball stage (238°).
Pour 1/3 over beaten egg whites and beat. Continue cooking remaining syrup to hard ball stage (270°).
Pour over egg mixture, beating constantly until solid enough to drop on wax paper and it stays put.

title: vidalia onions and cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion.
Place in a bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside.
Combine vinegar, water, pepper and sugar. Heat until sugar melts.
Pour over cucumbers and onion and refrigerate.

title: marsala chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart Corning Ware dish with cooking spray.
Coat chicken breasts with bread crumbs and place in dish.
Distribute 1 tablespoon margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Then pour 3/4 cup Marsala wine over chicken and bake for 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: "hippi" cornbread
directions: Grease 2 large black iron skillets.
Sprinkle
a thin layer of cornmeal and let brown.
Pour half of batter in skillet (first 7 ingredients).
Brown meat and onions together.
Layer over first half of batter.
Add peppers and add grated cheese.
Pour rest of batter and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dahi murgh (an indian dish)(chicken and yogurt curry)
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces, smaller pieces allow spices to penetrate better.
In an electric blender puree onion, garlic, ginger, fresh coriander or mint.
Heat oil in a heavy saucepan and fry the blended mixture, stirring for about 5 minutes.
Add turmeric, garam masala, salt and chili powder and fry for a further minute.
Stir in yogurt and tomatoes.
Fry until liquid dries up and the mixture is the consistency of thick puree.
Add chicken pieces, turning them in the spice mixture so they are coated on both sides, then turn the heat low, cover tightly and cook until chicken is tender.
If liquid from chicken has not evaporated by the time the flesh is cooked, uncover and raise heat to dry off excess liquid, stirring gently at the base of the pan to prevent burning.
Garnish with chopped herbs and serve with rice.

title: easy peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup Eagle Brand and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat; stir in peanuts.
Spread mixture into wax paper-lined 8-inch square pan.
In small saucepan, melt chocolate morsels, remaining Eagle Brand and margarine.
Spread chocolate mixture on top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel off paper and cut into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: caramel pecan pie
directions: Brown butter in large saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add corn syrup, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla, salt and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake an additional 40 minutes.
Let cool before serving.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening (or butter), sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Add dry mixture, raisins, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool 2 minutes on rack.

title: strawberry tunnel cream cake
directions: Invert cake onto serving plate.
Cut 1-inch slice crosswise from top of cake; set aside.
With sharp knife, cut around cake 1-inch from center hole and 1-inch from outer edge, leaving cake walls 1-inch thick.
Remove cake from center, leaving 1-inch thick base on bottom of cake.
Tear cake removed from center into bite sized pieces; reserve.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon brand lemon juice, extract and food coloring, if desired. Stir in torn cake pieces and chopped strawberries.
Fold in 1 cup whipped topping.
Fill cake cavity with strawberry mixture; replace top slice of cake.
Frost with remaining whipped topping. Chill 3 hours or freeze 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired.
Return leftovers to refrigerator or freezer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed.
Mix eggs, mayonnaise and cheese together.
Fold into broccoli.
Put into baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken about 45 minutes to an hour.
Remove from bone. Precook noodles.
Take at 9 x 11-inch casserole dish and butter it.
Mix all ingredients together, except cheese and paprika. Pour half of the mixture into the casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Then add other half of mixture.
Top with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for half an hour, covered.
Then bake half an hour, uncovered.

title: shrimp pasta
directions: Saut shrimp in margarine and juice of 2 lemons. Add chicken bouillon and water. Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch with 2 cups of milk. Add to shrimp mixture and cook until thickened. Add Morton's seasoning and then
add Monterey Jack cheese. Cook on low until cheese melts. Serve over spaghetti which has been cooked according to package directions and drained.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, nuts, cinnamon, salt, honey, flour and soda; you may have to mix with your hands.
Press thinly onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 300°.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on while hot.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add pineapple.
Congeal slightly. Add Pet milk, salad dressing, cottage cheese and pecans.

title: brownies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Stir in eggs and beat until creamy.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture and then add nuts.
Stir until well blended.

title: lemon seasoned chicken breast(lo-cal microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and parsley in small dish.
Arrange chicken breasts, bone side up on microwave-safe roasting rack, with meatiest portions to outside of dish.
Brush with half of seasoned mixture.
Microwave at High (100%) 5 minutes. Turn pieces over and brush with remaining mixture.
Microwave at High, 10 to 15 minutes or until meat near bone is no longer pink, rotating once during cooking.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes before serving, if desired.
Calories per serving 165, cholesterol 63 and sodium 132.

title: one pot meal
directions: Place frozen pork and beef roasts into covered baking pan; add onion and carrots and 1/2 cup water.
Put in oven at 350°.
Bake for 2 hours, then add potatoes and bake another 45 minutes. Remove meats and vegetables to make gravy.
Be sure to get all the brown around pan into your gravy.
Serve hot.

title: italian love cake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla together well.
Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Pour cake mix.
On top of cake mix spoon Ricotta cheese mixture.
Do not pour, spoon on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool in refrigerator.

title: veggie bits
directions: Lay rolls in large oblong pan and spread dough thinner to accomodate pan.
Beat together egg and water.
Use pastry brush and brush onto rolls before cooking.
Cook as directed on can.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine with sauces and soups.
Fry tortillas and cut in quarters.
Layer in casserole the tortillas, meat sauce, cheeses and end with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: little pizzas
directions: Put all ingredients in a double boiler, heat and stir until well mixed.
Spread on cocktail bread, put under boiler 5 to 10 minutes.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Blend cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion, peppers and mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate or shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Blend on high speed in blender for 15 to 30 seconds.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside, then combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs next. Gradually add flour mix, then chips.
Put on greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine
everything
except
the cheese and crackers in greased
9	x
13-inch pan.
Combine cheese and crackers, then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix well the Crisco, sugar, molasses and egg. Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Chill dough several hours. Roll in balls size of walnuts. Dip tops in sugar and flatten. Tops will crinkle. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. These are a soft cookie.

title: quick and easy hawaiian chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large casserole dish, arrange chicken and bake in the oven for 30 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and turn chicken over.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: sue's superb vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Garnish with fresh parsley. Serve with carrots, celery, turnip roots and raw cauliflower. Very good!

title: refrigerated dinner rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar until slightly creamy.
Pour boiling water into cup to dissolve all the shortening and add to creamed mixture.
Add lightly beaten eggs and stir, then add dissolved yeast.
Add flour, 3 cups at a time.
Stir until all flour is wet (do not try to remove the lumps).
Cover with waxed paper and aluminum foil and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup mixture, mayo and 2 eggs.
Place in casserole dish and cover with cheese.
In pan, brown Ritz crackers with the margarine.
Sprinkle crackers over casserole, then bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until cheese is brown and bubbly.

title: spam hash brown bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Combine potatoes, butter, salt, pepper and garlic powder. In separate bowl, combine Spam, soup, cheese, sour cream, milk, onion and chilies. Combine Spam and potato mixture. Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until heated. Makes 8 servings.

title: lime jello salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream.
Stir until blended in.
Add pineapple and juice.
Pour into mold or dish. Refrigerate until firm.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Cut various fruits into bite sized pieces and place in orange juice or mixture of fruit juices to chill.
Add bananas just before serving.
Can add nuts or coconut.

title: shrimp-crab gumbo
directions: In a large heavy Dutch oven or cast iron skillet over medium heat stir together the flour and oil, and cook, whisking constantly, until flour is a rich copper color (about 20 minutes--don't leave it or stop whisking for a second!).
Remove from heat immediately so it won't burn and proceed with gumbo recipe below.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together with mixer.
Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: old virginia applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Sift flour before measuring.
Use a little flour over raisins and nuts.
Add spices and salt to remaining flour. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add alternately with the flour, adding raisins and nuts last.
Pour into a floured and greased loaf pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple bean bake
directions: In a skillet, melt butter; add cubed apples and cook until tender.
Add brown and white sugar; stir and cook until sugar is melted.
Stir in cinnamon, catsup and molasses.
Add beans and mix well.
Pour mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 400° oven for about 1 hour.

title: molded perfection salad
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves. Remove from heat; stir in orange juice and Equal.
Chill about 25 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in vegetables and chives.
Pour into 1-quart mold, sprayed with nonstick coating. Chill about 4 hours or until set.
Unmold to serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce and let set 6 hours.

title: biscuit-topped hearty steak pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine steak, frozen vegetables and potatoes in prepared dish.
Stir in gravy, thyme and pepper.
Bake uncovered 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Increase oven temperature to 400°. Top with biscuits and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix and bake until golden brown at 350°, approximately 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows in mixing bowl. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; remove from oven and top with miniature marshmallows. Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: philly free 3-step pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar with electric mixer on medium. speed until well blended.
Blend in pumpkin, vanilla, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Add eggs, mix just until blended.
Do not over beat after adding eggs.
Spray 9 inch pie plate with cooking spray, sprinkle bottom with crumbs.
Pour cream cheese mixture into prepared pie plate.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll each piece in seasoned flour. Save any leftover mixture of flour.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: kool-aid play dough(child-approved)
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then add boiling water.
Stir and knead.
Store in plastic bag.
Smells great!

title: maple butter creams(excellent christmas candy)
directions: Boil sugar, Karo
and
water to 242° on candy thermometer. Keep crystals wiped down sides of pan.
Pour on an extra large cookie sheet
and cool to about lukewarm (I use a marble slab). Put butter
in
center
of cookie sheet or marble slab and start to work, stirring with metal or wooden spatula until cool enough to
work
with your hands.
This may take 2 people working together.
Form
small
balls
and coat with chocolate coating. Wrap each
ball
in wax paper.
Candy sets up better if cold outside and candy is placed outside to cool (in a safe place).

title: walnut bourbon balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, powdered sugar, cocoa and walnuts together.
Add corn syrup and bourbon or rum; mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: fusilli with seafood sauce(recipe from nina)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring frequently, until translucent, about 2 minutes.
Stir in salt, pepper and red pepper flakes, then add tomatoes with juice.
Increase heat to medium-high and simmer sauce, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in clams, scallops and basil. Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion; drain grease. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soup over beef mixture. Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 2 loaf pans or 4 (7 1/2 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch).
Stir together flour, sugar, baking soda, spices and 1 teaspoon salt.
Combine eggs, pumpkin, milk and oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Bake for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool pans on wire rack for 10 minutes, then remove from pans to finish cooling.
Enjoy.

title: creme brulee
directions: Heat cream in heavy saucepan just until bubbles form around the edge of pan.
In double boiler top, with electric mixer, beat yolks with granulated sugar until thick and light yellow. Gradually stir in cream.
Place over hot, not boiling, water. Cook, stirring constantly, until it coats a metal spoon, about 15 minutes. Add the vanilla.
Strain custard into a 1-quart shallow baking dish.
Refrigerate 8
hours or overnight.

title: butterscotch biscuit pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Combine first three ingredients. In a small saucepan, combine butterscotch morsels and shortening. Melt over hot water, stirring until smooth. Separate biscuit dough into 20 biscuits. Roll each biscuit between palms of hands to form an 8 inch strip. Coat strips with butterscotch mixture, then with crumb mixture. Coil each strip in greased muffin cup. Seal ends. Sprinkle with excess crumb mixture. Bake for 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Drizzle with glaze while pinwheels are warm. Makes 20.

title: better than sex cake #1
directions: Make white cake and let it cool thoroughly.
Beat Philadelphia cream cheese and add instant pudding.
Add 2 cups milk and mix together.
Spread over cake.
Drain pineapple and put on top of pudding mix.
Add Cool Whip, nuts and/or maraschino cherries.

title: italian muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, Italian seasoning and pepper.
Brush 12 medium muffin cups with about 3 tablespoons margarine mixture.
Mix baking mix, milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds.
If dough is too sticky, gradually mix in enough baking mix (up to 1/4 cup) to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto surface dusted with baking mix.
Roll in baking mix to coat.

title: shrimp muffins
directions: Halve muffins.
Butter slightly.
Wash shrimp in salt water and drain.
Dab with paper towels.
Dice in fine pieces.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil, cider vinegar and salt for dressing.
Add drained beans and onion.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 6 or more hours.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat cocoa, butter and Coke to boiling. Put flour, baking soda and sugar in a bowl; sift, then add heated cocoa mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Grease pan and pour in batter.
Add marshmallows.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in medium-sized Dutch oven and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, milk and vanilla and mix well.
Pour this mixture into Dutch oven containing oleo (melted).
Pour in peaches and bake for 1 hour.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, adding a little buttermilk.
Add this to the soda which has been dissolved in a little hot water.
Put into this enough water to make smooth.
Add beaten eggs and remainder of flour and jam.
Beat all well, adding last the nuts and spices.
Bake in layers at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use a caramel icing.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Will keep in refrigerator for a week.
Marinate a few days before serving.

title: ham-broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in margarine in a large skillet until onion is tender.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: italian coconut cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, egg yolks, margarine, and shortening. Add flour, baking soda, buttermilk, coconut, pecans, and vanilla. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together, serve with veggies.

title: picnic cake
directions: Mix first two ingredients in boiling water and set aside until totally cool.
Mix together sugar, margarine, eggs, flour, salt and baking powder, then add to cooled date mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
On top of batter, sprinkle the brown sugar, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: oven shake 'n bake mix
directions: Dip any meat, fish or chicken in the mix for pan frying or oven baking.

title: hearty holiday soup
directions: Wash all beans thoroughly.
Place in large container.
Cover with water and add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning drain.
Add 2 quarts water and about 1/2 pound ham or ham hocks.
Bring to a boil.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Then add onion, tomato, chili powder, lemon juice and salt and pepper.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Makes very large pot of soup.
Serve with French bread or crackers, green salad or relish plate.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan; simmer.
If desired, add red hot sauce, salt, pepper and minced onion to taste.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix hamburger, carrot, green pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, egg, cracker crumbs, pepper, salt, hamburger seasoning and catsup until well combined.
Shape the mixture into a loaf; place in a lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: festive potato pancakes
directions: Wash potatoes in cold water and peel.
Dry potatoes and shred thinly.
Mix all ingredients with shredded potatoes.
Make into patties and brown in hot oil until crisp on both sides.

title: orange bran muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into oiled muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
You may want to halve this recipe.
It stores in the refrigerator well.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Place in cupcake papers in cupcake pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: micro-no-fail-divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and salt in a 2 quart casserole.
Cook in microwave for 19 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes or 260° on a candy thermometer.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Pour hot syrup gradually over egg whites, beating at high speed for about 12 minutes or until thick and candy begins to lose gloss.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add syrup, sugar, nuts, salt and vanilla. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake 50 minutes in a 325° oven.
The pecans will float to the top forming a crust.

title: white grape splash
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl or pot.
If you wish to make an iced ring mold, fill an 8 or 10-inch ring mold with some of the punch mixture and freeze until solid.
(If you are using champagne in the punch, be sure to allow the mold to freeze overnight.)
Serve in a chilled punch bowl with ice or a ring mold.
Yields 1 1/4 gallons.

title: bean salad
directions: Cook and drain	all beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with paprika and refrigerate.

title: divinity
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water to soft ball stage.
Pour one-half of this over stiffly beaten egg whites, returning remaining half to heat to cook to "crack stage."
Continue beating egg whites. Pour remaining syrup slowly over egg whites, beating constantly, until candy holds its shape.
Add flavoring and chopped nuts. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with sugar and lemon juice; add celery, nuts and raisins. Fold in mayonnaise and chill.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and add other ingredients.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: spanish stew
directions: Brown hamburger and remove grease.
Add onion, tomato sauce, tomato paste and green peppers.
Simmer slowly.
Add peas at last minute and just heat peas through until hot.
Serve.

title: chicken nuggets(microwave)
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place margarine in glass pie plate and microwave on High 1 minute.
Put dry stuffing in a small paper bag.
Crush with rolling pin.
Combine stuffing crumbs, cheese and oregano.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine, then roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange in single layer in a 2-quart rectangular dish.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes. Redistribute pieces midway through cooking.
Let stand 3 minutes. Serves 4.

title: peanut butter lover's pie
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Stir in sugar.
Add milk and butter. Beat flour into 1/4 cup milk until smooth and stir into mixture. Place in double boiler and cook over hot water until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked shell and top with meringue.

title: chicken and spanish quiche
directions: Pierce pastry shell with fork.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Toss chicken, cheese, spinach and onion.
Spoon into shell.
Stir eggs, mayonnaise, milk, basil and pepper together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6
to 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water, put into dish and into refrigerator until set.
Cover with sour cream and serve.

title: cheesed mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2-inch quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: capt. boomer's dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, rub 2 tablespoons of butter on all sides and bottom.
Freeze for 10 minutes.
Mix graham crackers, cinnamon and 4 tablespoons butter.
Press mixture on bottom and all sides of pan.
Freeze for 15 minutes.
Layer softened ice cream (about 1 1/2 inches thick) on top of crust.
Freeze for 30 minutes, or until frozen.
Layer almonds, then candy, then pour chocolate syrup, covering the top.
Serve with Cool Whip on individual servings.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all ingredients, except spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix wet and dry dressings together.
Cook spaghetti; drain. Run cold water over.
Chop vegetables.
Mix vegetables, spaghetti and cheese.
Add dressing.
Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Really good!

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt, add to melted margarine.
Mix well.
Add egg yolks and beat after each one.
Add milk and vanilla flavoring.
Cook until well thickened.
Make 2 layers of bananas and wafers, beginning with wafers and ending with bananas. Cover each layer with pudding mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread on top of pudding, sealing edges around dish.
Bake until egg whites are brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Save several orange sections for top.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Top with reserved sections before serving.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter; set aside.
Beat together eggs, sugar and corn syrup.
Add chocolate mixture (and nuts). Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Put milk, onion, cheese, flour and margarine in blender. Cover and process or grind until smooth.
Layer half of potatoes in 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour half of milk mixture over potatoes.
Add remaining potatoes.
Pour remaining milk mixture over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken stew
directions: Combine chicken and broth in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
6 cups (about 137 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, ginger and salt.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix and add pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (or until done).
Makes 2 pies.

title: leprechaun salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine the cabbage, grapes, apples, raisins and yogurt; mix well.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place nuts and/or raisins in bottom of pan. Combine sugar and cinnamon in Ziploc bag.
Place biscuit pieces into bag and shake.
Layer biscuit pieces in pan.

title: noodles
directions: Beat together eggs, salt, Milnot and oil.
Add flour.
Divide dough in two parts and roll dough paper thin. Let dry 30 to 45 minutes.
Cut noodles in desired width.

title: freezer strawberry jam
directions: Stir strawberries (crushed) and sugar in a bowl.
Bring water and pectin to boil.
Let boil one minute.
Add to berries and sugar.
Stir for 3 minutes.
Put in jars or cups.
Set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Now ready to freeze.
Makes 6 half pints.

title: peach fritters
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Stir in beaten egg, milk and melted butter.
Stir only until mixed.
Fold in peaches.
Drop by small teaspoons into hot Crisco oil and deep fry for about 2 minutes until nicely browned and crisp.
Drain on a brown paper sack and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: "puppy" chow for people
directions: Over low heat or in microwave, melt the chocolate chips, peanut butter and oleo.
Pour over it the cereal.
Mix to coat; put all into a large paper bag with 1 cup confectioners sugar on bottom.
Put 1 cup confectioners sugar on top, as well, and shake well.
(This is impossible to stay away from!)

title: spiced ham loaf
directions: Soften crumbs in milk; combine meat, seasonings, crumbs and egg.
Mix and pack in loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: crustworthy meat loaf
directions: Thaw bread as package directs.
Make meat loaf using the ground beef, bread or cracker crumbs, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take out and drain well.
Press bread dough onto bottom of greased larger pan.
Wrap the dough around over the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, eggs and oil.
In a separate bowl mix together flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate flour and milk into sugar mixture.
Beat well.
Add flavorings and beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 greased loaf pans (4 x 8-inches).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Fry celery and onion in oil.
Add broccoli, broken and cooked until tender.
Add rice, cheese, soup and salt to taste.
Mix well and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Garnish and serve.

title: no bake fudgies
directions: Mix together in a saucepan the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Boil the mixture for exactly one minute.
Remove from heat and add the vanilla, coconut, oats and peanut butter.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Store in covered container when completely cool.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and cream cheese.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Season squirrel with pepper. Simmer in water with onion for 2 hours. Add corn, limas, potatoes, tomatoes and sugar; simmer for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar, 2 tablespoons of cocoa and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Mix brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Sprinkle over batter.
Pour water over entire batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread.
Spread slices with oleo.
Place in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage until brown; stir to crumble.
Drain.
Spoon over the bread; sprinkle with cheese. Combine eggs, half and half and salt; mix well.
Pour over cheese. Cover and chill overnight.

title: buttercream icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening with an electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Keep icing covered until ready to use.
Can be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator for 2 weeks.
Re-whip before using.
Makes 3 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pineapple into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherry filling over pineapple.
Pour cake mix over pie filling and spread pecans over cake.
Spread a thin layer of margarine over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: outrageous blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place liners in muffin cups or grease and flour pan cups.
In large bowl, place flour, sugar, shortening, milk, eggs, baking powder, salt, vanilla and water. Blend at low speed for 2 minutes; scrape sides of bowl and mix at high speed for 6 minutes.
Spoon batter into muffin pan cups, filling each 1/2 full.
Add 6 to 10 blueberries to the batter in each cup, mixing in several and leaving some at top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean and dry.
Remove from oven and cool in pan for 10 minutes, then turn out and allow muffins to cool completely.

title: wedding cake icing
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Beat until smooth enough to spread.
Produces a creamy icing which does not harden.

title: half pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Cream the eggs, one or two at a time with the mixture.
Add the flour.
Add the flavoring.
Bake the cake at 300° on the bottom rack of the oven for just over 1 hour.

title: chick-a-bobs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut chicken thighs into chunks.
Cut green pepper, onion and tomato into wedges.
Alternate chicken and vegetable on skewer.
Place on baking sheet in oven 30 to 35 minutes or cook outside on grill until thoroughly cooked, about 15 minutes per side.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream together the butter or oleo, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add the eggs, flour, vanilla, baking powder and soda.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all well.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours. Drop by tablespoon. Bake until slightly browned.

title: dumplings
directions: Dissolve oleo in hot water.
Add salt and flour; stir well. Chill.
Roll thin on floured board.
Cut in squares and place on cookie sheet with wax paper between layers.
Put in freezer.
Put loose in freezer bags.
Cook in hot beef or chicken broth.

title: sausage and egg breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Separate crescent dough and place in lightly greased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and sides to form crust and seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust; sprinkle with potatoes. Top with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until egg is cooked.

title: spaghetti squash italian
directions: Spoon
out
seed of spaghetti squash and place cut side down in	1-inch water in metal pan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour until soft.
Drain.

title: plain cookies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on baking sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: fry cakes
directions: Cream egg, sugar and Crisco well; add milk and sifted flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with cutter and cook 3 to 5 minutes in hot Crisco.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones.
Place in casserole dish. Pour peas over chicken.
Mix soups and milk together.
Pour over peas.
Mix stuffing mix, butter and broth; pour over mixture and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: jubilee fruit cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend milk, honey, marshmallows, salt and spices.
Beat in prepared fruits and nuts.
Work into mixture 6 cups graham cracker crumbs and brandy.
If mixture will not hold together, add more cracker crumbs.
Press firmly into buttered 2-quart ring mold or two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover with foil.
Chill in refrigerator several days to blend flavors.
Makes 2 1/2 pound cake.
Freezes well.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle cheese on top as you take out of oven.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix pudding with 3 quarts of milk, then add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: grated buttered beets
directions: Grate beets.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add grated beets, salt, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Fill 2/3 full in greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve plain or with sugar-orange juice glaze.
Batter keeps at least 1 week in refrigerator.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine water and milk.
Add pudding, mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 Cup pudding mixture into serving bowl. top with 1/3 of the nilla wafers, then bananas.
Repeat until top layer is pudding.
I sometimes add plain cool whip to the top as icing and dried banana chips as a garnish.
Chill.

title: fruit slices
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to mixture gradually and beat well.
Reserve 1 cup of this dough for topping.

title: easy bake chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breast in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine jelly and remaining ingredients; spoon over chicken.
Turn chicken to coat all sides.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover; baste with sauce. Bake, uncovered, an additional 25 minutes.

title: maude's apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs, apples, dates, raisins and nuts.
Mix together dry ingredients; add to other mixture.
Pour into 1 greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: casserole meal
directions: Place in casserole in order given.
Pour tomato soup over all. Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake until brown.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add water and simmer until tender. Add cooked noodles and soup with 1 can water.
Mix well, then pour into buttered casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake in slow oven (350°) about 1 hour.

title: greek cheese squares
directions: Butter bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place first layer of fillo; baste with butter and repeat 3 more layers with basted butter between each one.
Mix all cheeses and the eggs.
Spread evenly over layers.
Cover cheese mixture with 5 layers of fillo, basting between each one.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let set for 15 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Mix together turkey, celery, almonds, salt, onion, lemon juice and mayonnaise and spread in casserole dish.
Sprinkle potato chips and cheese over top.
Cook at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: something fun
directions: Place flour in a bowl.
Make a well in center.
Drop eggs, water and salt into it.
Work into flour with one hand and knead until smooth and elastic.
Pinch off small balls and roll each out very thin as though for noodle strips.
Fry in deep oil until light brown.
Drain on brown paper.
When cool, sift powdered sugar over.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until light brown on top.

title: beefless meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl; mix until well blended.
Press into bottom of lightly oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon jello pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in one large bowl and beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan and cook at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave cake there until cool to touch.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with cheese. Cut potatoes in half lengthwise. Place potatoes, cut side down, on cheese mixture. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cornmeal-cheese straws
directions: Beat butter and cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer until creamy.
Add water, beating well.
Combine flour and remaining ingredients; gradually add to cheese mixture, beating until blended.
Use a cookie press to shape dough into strips, following manufacturer's instructions.
(If a small serrated disc is not available, place a small piece of tape over each side of the serrated disc to leave a 3/4-inch opening.)
Place strips on ungreased baking sheets; cut into 2-inch strips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Store in airtight containers, placing wax paper between layers.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream sugars, eggs and butter together.
Add dry pudding mix, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas morning rolls
directions: Grease a tube (Bundt) pan.
Arrange rolls in pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over top.
Cook butter, brown sugar and cinnamon over low heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture bubbles.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over rolls.
Cover tightly with foil.
Place on cookie sheet and place on countertop overnight.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain excess fat.
Mix ground beef with tomato sauce.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into bottom of baking dish. Cook noodles and layer over beef mixture.
Layer sour cream over noodles.
Layer grated cheese over sour cream.
Layer onion over cheese.
Add remaining beef mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread(1 loaf)
directions: Beat until fluffy sugar, oil, eggs, lemon peel and orange extract.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes in greased loaf pan.
(Line bottom of pan with wax paper.) Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place pork chops in casserole dish; top with potatoes and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour cream of mushroom soup over vegetables and pork chops.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: best ever scalloped pineapple
directions: Drain can of pineapple, reserving 1 cup of juice.
Cook together juice, sugar, flour and margarine until thickened. Generously butter an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Cube bread and place in casserole and mix with drained chunk pineapple.
Pour thickened pineapple sauce over mixture, gently blend in.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: stroganoff
directions: Dredge steak in flour.
Combine steak, broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper in 2 1/2 quart microproof casserole.
Push meat to center of casserole; set aside.
Wipe mushrooms with damp towel.
Cut into thick slices.
Arrange mushrooms and onion around meat.
Cover with casserole lid and cook on 80 for 10-13 minutes or until tender.
Stir in sour cream.
4 servings.
Total cooking time:
10-13 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Open 2 or 3 cans of pork and beans. Pour into dish.
Add other ingredients (onion, syrup, brown sugar, ketchup).
Mix together.
Add 2 or 3 slices of bacon on top.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: green goddess salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Beat Jell-O and cream cheese together.
Add milk mixture. Beat until smooth. Add pineapple, including juice. Fold in whipping cream and mayonnaise. Add nuts. Pour into bowl and chill.

title: cottage cheese dressing
directions: Blend in blender or food processor.

title: gladys' pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately to preceeding mixture.
Add flavorings. Place in cold stove and turn oven to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: granny's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Pour in a large baking pan.

title: imitation crab bake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add 1/2 of cracker mixture (crackers broken into quarters and mixed with margarine) in a one-quart baking dish. Place 1/2 of the crab on top of the crackers.
Add remaining crackers and crab in the same manner.
Top with paprika and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: chile con queso dip for nacho chips
directions: Mix all ingredients in a slow cooking pot.
Cover and cook on low 2 to 3 hours.
Serve hot from crock-pot.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: grandma's irish bread
directions: Knead all dry ingredients thoroughly with buttermilk.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
If you do not have buttermilk, add a little vinegar to regular milk and let sit one hour.

title: bachelor's delight
directions: Start with a basic three-egg omelet.
To this, add the remaining ingredients.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together.
Eat within 1 1/2 hours of making.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 2-quart pan.
Add small amount of milk. Stir to mix well.
Add remaining milk.
Stir constantly over medium heat.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir in and mix thoroughly.
Serve over hot biscuits that have been buttered.

title: "cheese balls"
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add chopped onion blades and 1/2 of the chopped beef.
Roll into balls, then roll the balls in the other 1/2 of the beef.

title: super rolls
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Place shortening, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Add lukewarm water and stir well. Stir in beaten egg and dissolved yeast. Add flour all at once.
Beat to make a soft dough.
Make into rolls.
Let rise about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or
until brown.
Makes 15 to 18 rolls.

title: ice cream jell-o
directions: Sherbet, ice milk, or frozen yogurt can be substituted for ice cream.

title: icicle cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers into 1/2-inch strips. Soak in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight. Do not use aluminum pan. Stir gently in lime water to keep lime from settling in bottom. Remove from lime water; discard water. Rinse 3 times in fresh cold water until water is clear. Soak 3 hours in fresh ice water. Keep adding ice cubes to keep water cold or place in refrigerator.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop 8 quarts popcorn.
Do not salt.
Combine sugar, Karo, butter, salt and vanilla and bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Mixture will then become foamy.
Stir and pour over popcorn.
Put in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Every 15 minutes take out and mix well.
When done, break up popcorn.

title: six layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch oven. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter and layer other ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until light brown.
Serves 36 bars.

title: chilled fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit separately.
Mix together marshmallows, sour cream, mayonnaise and pineapple.
Add mandarin oranges and fruit cocktail.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: real spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over moderate heat.
Add rice and stir quickly to coat with oil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until light brown.
Add onion and cook about 5 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly, until rice is browned and onion is soft.
Place garlic, cumin, tomatoes, salt and pepper in a blender; blend at high speed until tomatoes and garlic are well broken up.
Add to rice along with broth.
Cover, bring to boil and cook 15 minutes. Add parsley and garbanzos and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer until all liquid has been absorbed.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 9 cups.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Be sure to use peach pie filling as this is the binder.
Other types of fruit can be substituted.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Gradually beat in sugar, then oil.
Combine all dry ingredients, adding alternately with zucchini.
Stir in raisins or dates, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake on lowest rack at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool on wire racks for 10 minutes.
Freezes well after cool.

title: almond chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Cook rice according to directions.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Place in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with grated cheese while hot.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in blender; blend well. Slowly add cup salad oil until thick. Pour into jar with tight-fitting lid and chill. Shake well before serving. Yields 2 cups.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; set aside.
Separate eggs and beat yolks; set aside egg whites.
Put milk in microwave (on High) for 4 1/2 minutes (until hot).
Stir in dry ingredients and microwave 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave another 4 minutes (will get thick).
Pour hot mixture over egg yolks, little at a time, mixing well while stirring.
Put egg mixture back into hot mixture and microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Add oleo and vanilla and set aside while making meringue.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/2 cup sugar slowly.
Beat until it peaks.
Add almond flavor (at least 1 teaspoon).
Put in baked pie crust and bake in regular oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Cook 3 hours or until thick.
Add sugar and cinnamon to taste.

title: boltanas
directions: On a round pizza pan, spread the refried beans.

Mix the sour cream with the taco seasoning mix. Spread over the beans. Sprinkle chopped onion over mixture. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese next. Top with cut olives of both kinds, chopped green pepper and chopped tomato. Dip your chips!

title: cajun corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large saucepan. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 4 servings.
Has 150 calories, fat free. Try the hominy, you'll be surprised.

title: english toffee
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients until amber colored, stirring continually.
Pour onto cookie sheet; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When melted, spread evenly.
Let cool, then crack and serve.

title: cheese shrimp casserole
directions: Cut each slice of bread diagonally and dip in butter.
Arrange 1/2 in bottom of an 8-inch square dish. Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese, onion, parsley and shrimp on top of bread slices.
Repeat bread and cheese layers. Beat eggs, salt, mustard, milk and sour cream. Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until puffed.

title: wes' thirst quencher
directions: Mix the honey, apple cider vinegar and ginger in a little warm water. Add to a large glass of cold water.

title: carrot bread
directions: Grease 2 - 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pans.
