Into a large mixing bowl measure eggs, sugar, vegetable oil, vanilla, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt.
Beat 1/2 minute on low speed scraping constantly.
Beat 1 minute on medium speed scraping constantly until smooth.
Stir in flour gradually, then mix in remaining ingredients.
Divide batter between 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool in pans 5-10 minutes then remove and cool thoroughly.
Freeze well.

title: raisin pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, vinegar, cinnamon and butter.
Stir in raisins and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Pour filling into a 9 inch unbaked pie crust and bake at 300 degrees for 35 minutes.
Serve with cool whip.
Serves 4-6.

title: cornish hen and rice bake
directions: Using a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine uncooked rice with seasonings, celery, mushrooms and water.
Dot with butter.
Cut hens in half lengthwise.
Place, cut-side down, over rice mixture. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour covered with foil.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sopa de papas (mexican potato soup)
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, parsley, salt and pepper; drain.
Add bacon and drippings, milk and cream.
Heat to almost boiling.
(May need to add a little water.)
Sprinkle cheese over individual bowls of soup.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries; set aside.
Cherries should be sliced.
Squeeze juice from 2 lemons and set aside.

title: chicken-n-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans according to package.
Save 1/4 cup of liquid after cooking.
Combine soup and liquid from green beans with green beans, sprouts and water chestnuts.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove casserole after baking; top with French fried onion rings, then broil until brown.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Pierce pastry shell thoroughly with a fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
Mix the ingredients together thoroughly and pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; let cool.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch container; let congeal.
Mix the cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Mix all together; spread on top.
Chill and serve.
It is better not to get it too thick.

title: aroma of christmas
directions: Simmer in water in an uncovered pan or crock-pot.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Whip the cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
In another bowl, mix the pudding mix and milk.
Put both mixtures together. Add Cool Whip.
Put half the crushed Oreos in bottom of bowl.
Put filling on Oreos, then top with rest of the crushed Oreos.
Chill and eat.

title: chicken mull
directions: Cook hen in small amount of water.
Debone and cut in small pieces.
Cook slowly in stock (add water if necessary) with onions.
Add milk, butter, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
Add crackers until Mull reaches desired consistency.

title: grandma wheeler's bread
directions: Place the first three ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
Over potato mix, pour warm water and sprinkle yeast in water. Let mushroom, stir, add oil.
Add flour until no longer soupy.
Make stiff dough by edging in flour and kneading until elastic.
Add a little oil once elastic, turn roll of dough over and cover with a warm damp cloth; let rise.
Punch down, roll into loaves, place in pan.
Let rise to double.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pea and cheese salad
directions: Have peas thoroughly chilled before mixing.
Dice cheese and combine all ingredients.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples. Bake 30 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Bring to a boil, cook until mixture forms firm ball when a little is dropped in cold water.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff. Slowly pour boiling syrup in a fine stream over the egg whites, beating at high speed.
Beat until mixture passes glossy stage and holds its shape.
Drop from the tips of two knives onto waxed paper.
Coloring may be added during last stage of beating.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Serve with fresh raw vegetables.

title: spun gold bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Heat milk, water and margarine to 120° to 130°.
Add to flour mixture; add eggs.
Blend 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour and knead.
Grease bowl and let dough rise.
Punch down.
Form 2 loaves and place in greased bread pans.
Let rise and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: garlicky chicken wings
directions: Using either wings, cutlets or chicken parts, rinse and pat dry.
Separate cloves of peeled garlic; place garlic, olive oil and hot sauce in blender or food processor and puree.
Do not cut garlic, leave cloves whole, they puree much better whole.
Combine bread crumbs and grated cheese with pepper.
Dip wings in puree (garlic).
Roll in bread crumbs, one piece at a time.
Oil shallow baking pan.
In single layer bake in preheated 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until crisp and brown.

title: cheap brown eggless cake
directions: Mix brown sugar, water, raisins or dried apples, salt and shortening. Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Let cool for a while, then add flour, soda and spices.
Put in a pan and bake.

title: taco pie
directions: Layer Fritos, chili, cheese and onions in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: creamsicle(drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Enjoy; taste like cream popsicles.

title: chip dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together until creamy.
Serve ice cold.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Saute until golden brown the ham, 1/2 stick margarine or butter and bell pepper.
Boil until tender the potatoes, celery, carrots and onions.
Mix and cook until thick the milk, 1 stick margarine or butter and flour.
Mix Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese in sauce until melted.

title: pickled beets
directions: Trim top and bottom of beets and wash dirt off of them.
Put beets in a large enough soup pot so they can be covered with water. Bring beets to a boil.
Boil beets for 60 minutes.
Pick out one of the biggest beets and cut in half to determine if all of them are well done inside.
If they are not, boil for another 10 minutes and check again.
Repeat this process until the beets are done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, mix soup, milk, chicken and vegetables (if desired) together. Add noodles and mix well. Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with grated cheese and paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bacon, egg and cheese muffins
directions: Fry at least 6 slices of bacon (will probably need more). Remove bacon from skillet and drain grease.
Then, fry eggs, being sure to break the yolks.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When eggs are almost done, top each with a slice of cheese and let melt.
Toast split muffins.
Top muffins with eggs and bacon.
Mustard is good on them, or use whatever dressing you prefer.

title: garden pest insecticide
directions: Mix solution and store in airtight jar.
When ready to use, add 1 to 2 1/2 teaspoons solution to 1 cup water.
Spray on plants, covering all leaf and stem surfaces.

title: almond gingersnaps(yields 48)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter in bowl; add sugar, molasses, spices and soda and mix well.
Stir in almonds. Sprinkle 1/2 cup flour onto work surface.
Add remaining 3 cups flour gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into 2 long rolls; wrap each in wax paper.
Chill or freeze until ready to bake.
Cut with sharp knife into thin slices.
Place on greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: country club squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water.
Drain and mash. Combine squash, sour cream, salt, pepper and basil.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce, cheese, butter and paprika.
Spread over squash mixture. Top with bacon.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or microwave 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in the bottom of a 9 x 12 pan. Mix rest of ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan. Cream shortening and brown sugar until light.
Add egg and molasses; beat well.
Stir together the flour, ginger, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the 1/2 cup boiling water, beating after each addition.
Pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix all ingredients, but soup, into square (8 x 8-inch) pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares and roll in flour.
Brown in oleo.
Place in baking dish.
Mix soup and about 1/2 can water. Pour over steak.
Bake in slow oven 2 to 3 hours at 250°.

title: tuna fish boats
directions: Mix all ingredients and spoon into hot dog buns.
Place side by side in casserole and heat in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: irresistible brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Remove from heat (or melt in microwave).
Add sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla.
Stir with spoon until batter is well blended and smooth.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until set.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: mango nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add eggs, butter, mango and lemon juice.	Mix well.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into buttered loaf pan. Cook 60 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on a rack.
Best cut the next day.

title: easy broccoli
directions: In skillet, combine water and soup mix.
Add broccoli. Simmer, covered until broccoli is done.

title: grandma's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in hand cranked or electric one gallon ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Save to fold into soup later.
Cook potatoes until done. Add carrots, corn and chicken.
Add eggs to soup at last minute.
Serve over noodles.

title: bumble bee coffee cake
directions: Butter Bundt pan or 10-inch cake pan.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces each and drop pieces into pan.
Bring to a boil the brown sugar, cinnamon and butter, then add nuts, then stop.
Pour mixture over biscuit pieces.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn upside down.

title: creamy italian dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender on high speed until smooth and creamy.
Chill before serving.
Yields 2 1/2 cups. Contains 8 1/2 calories per serving.

title: easy creamed cheese dessert
directions: Cream with mixer
in
mixing
bowl the cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.	Add
instant pudding mix and cold milk.
Blend until smooth and thick.
Then add Cool Whip.
Blend until well mixed. Pour into
graham
cracker	crust and chill.
Then top with your favorite fruit filling.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Grease a casserole dish and add cut up potatoes.
Mix mayonnaise, margarine, sour cream, chives and crumbled bacon over potatoes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese (to taste).
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and potatoes are hot through.

title: dad's special casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and seasonings.
Layer half noodles, meat sauce and cheese in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; return to oven until cheese melts.
Serve this with stewed tomatoes.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix as listed.
Store in jar in refrigerator.

title: low-fat french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into French fry matchsticks.
Spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Combine the egg whites and Cajun seasoning in a bowl.
Add the potatoes and mix to coat. Spread the coated potatoes into a single layer on the cookie sheet.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until the fries are crispy and golden.
Turn them halfway through the baking so they will be an even brown.
Serve hot with nonfat ketchup.

title: broccoli mushroom soup
directions: Clean and cut broccoli.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender. Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Add bouillon, stirring with a wire whip and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli, mushrooms (sliced), half and half and spices.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: medium thick chili
directions: Blend well.
Add 3 cans light red kidney beans.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Bake chicken to 400° for one hour until tender.
After chicken cools, shred it into bite-size pieces.
Combine soups, milk and green chili sauce.
Grease casserole.
Layer chicken, tortea, sauce and cheese.
End with cheese.
Continue with layers until ingredients are gone.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours until cheese browns.
Uncover last 10 minutes.
Make night before, and bake before serving.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks in saucepan.
Combine sugar and flour; add to eggs.
Gradually add milk.
Mix until smooth.
Add lemon rind and slowly add lemon juice, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until filling is smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Drain well.
Add next five ingredients.
Melt butter (3/4 stick) in frying pan; add stuffing and mix well.
Pack into bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Reserve some stuffing to sprinkle on top. Pour squash mixture over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Dot rest of butter (1/4 stick) on top of the casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: polish style cabbage (kapusta)
directions: Cut up cabbage.
In deep pot, put cabbage, tomatoes and water to cover.
Put on heat and bring to boil.
Lower heat.
Add sauerkraut, caraway seeds and salt.
Stir occasionally.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: On the bottom of a Pyrex dish, layer the first 7 ingredients in the order given.
Cover entire dish with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Garnish with sliced black olives.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar and water together.
Add to other ingredients.

title: ants on a log
directions: Put peanut butter on celery.
Put raisins on top.
Enjoy!

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and blend well.
Pour into baking dish or loaf pan.
Make a sauce with the remaining 3 ingredients and spread over the top of the ham loaf.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and set overnight.
Scoop out center of loaf; cut bread into 1 inch squares.
Place dip into center of loaf and serve with bread squares.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onions until done.
Add to melted Velveeta.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn chips or taco chips.
I put mine in the crock-pot.
Hot.
Serves many.

title: light bread biscuits
directions: Mix like biscuits.
Let rise until double in size.
Work down. Make biscuits.
Before done, brush top with melted butter.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and vanilla; beat well. Stir flour with baking powder; blend into creamed mixture.
Divide in half.
Cover; chill for 1 hour.
On a lightly floured surface, roll each half to 1/8-inch thickness for thin cookies or 1/4-inch thickness for thick cookies.
Cut into desired shapes with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake thin cookies at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Bake thick cookies 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen thin cookies or 3 dozen thick cookies.

title: swiss steak
directions: Peel and chop the onion and carrot finely.

Heat the oil in a large frypan or saucepan; add the onion and cook until the onion is clear or translucent. Add the minced beef and saut, using a wooden spoon to break up the mince so it is nice and fine.
When the mince is thoroughly browned, stir through the flour and cook for 1 minute. Add the tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, carrot, peas, corn and herbs. Stir thoroughly.

Gradually add the stock and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and cover, simmering for 10 to 15 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. The mixture should be quite thick. Remove and discard the bouquet garni or whole bay leaf and set mixture aside.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, milk and sugar.
Pour into pan on top of margarine.
Add pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Blend shortening, sugar and eggs.
Cream well.
Add cranberries, nuts and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to egg mixture.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: whipped potatoes
directions: Heat potatoes with water to cover until boiling.
Lower heat and cook
until
fork-tender,
about
to
20 minutes. Drain. Return to heat and cook, uncovered, 2 minutes or until all water is evaporated.
Pour
potatoes
in
a large bowl and mash with rest
of
ingredients.
With electric mixer, beat on high for 3 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Mix vegetables, onion, green pepper and cheese on pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients with mixer for about 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour into pie plate over other ingredients.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean and pie is golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Prepare potatoes.
Drain salmon; remove bones and skin. Flake salmon into potatoes.
Add egg, pepper and crumbs.
Mix well; shape into patties. (Add more crumbs if needed.)
Pan fry in vegetable oil about 5 minutes on each side.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Start with an 8 x 8-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Starting with cabbage, layer all in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or more until piping hot.

title: savannah beans and greens soup
directions: In a soup pot, combine onions and garlic in 2 cups of the stock. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare collard greens by removing coarse stems. Stack leaves and slice them thinly crosswise and then cut through stack lengthwise twice. Add the greens, tomatoes, peas, additional stock, vinegar, brown sugar, thyme, allspice and Tabasco. Simmer 15 minutes. Stir in rice and cook 3-5 minutes. Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve with cornbread.

title: cocktail franks in wine sauce
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onions for 3 minutes or until clear.
Blend in flour.
Add wine, stirring steadily to boiling point.
Mix in salt, thyme and sauce.
Brown franks in skillet. Drain and add to sauce.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Serve in casserole or chafing dish.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Combine hamburger and onion soup mix.
Make small meatballs and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Mix together with soups, taco sauce, tomato sauce, chilies and rice.
Layer Doritos and meat mixture. Repeat.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain, rinse, and drain spaghetti.
Pour the Italian dressing over the noodles and stir well. Set aside.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain and flake salmon and combine with lemon juice, onion, horseradish and parsley.
Mix well and chill.
When chilled, shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts or cracker crumbs.
Store in fridge until ready to use.

title: dipping batter for fish
directions: Put eggs into small bowl of electric mixer; beat on medium speed for 1 minute.
Add milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to milk mixture.
Add shortening.
Beat on low speed until blended.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Make bread filling as you do for fowl.
Mix filling, sausage and peas.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with pork gravy.

title: frito chili pie
directions: Crush 2 cups Fritos.
Spread in baking dish.
Arrange chopped onions and 1/2 of cheese on chips.
Spread chili over onions and cheese.
Top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Separate each biscuit into two pieces.
Using a muffin pan, cover the bottom and sides of each hole in the pan using one piece of biscuit.
Be sure to spread your biscuit thinly, as it will rise.
Layer sauce, sausage, hamburger, bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and pour over oyster crackers. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Blend butter and sugar together.
Add 1 egg at a time, blending.
Then add a little of the flour at a time.
Blend very well.
Then add vanilla flavoring.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream eggs and sugar together; melt oleo.
Mix with eggs and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, and 3/4 can of coconut.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell; sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Beat egg whites and water.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt and pepper.
Dip cutlets in egg mix, then coat with crumb mix.
Repeat for all pieces of veal.
Place on waxed paper and chill for at least 1 hour.
Fry cutlets in heated oil.
Brown about 2 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add applesauce with which soda has been mixed.
Mix flour, salt and spices, sifted together, then add raisins to this to coat them. Beat hard until well blended into sugar and Crisco.
Bake in a 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick and easy parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Place Italian dressing in bowl; dip chicken strips in dressing. Mix bread crumbs and cheese together; dip the dressing coated chicken into the mixture. Lay chicken side by side along greased pan; pour remaining dressing and bread crumbs over the chicken. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In large pan, saute chicken and oil until chicken is lightly browned.
Add broth, vegetables and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 10 minutes. Fluff with a fork.
Add soy sauce to individual servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and cool (reserving broth).
Cook spaghetti in reserved broth and margarine.
Add onion when spaghetti is almost done.
Add tomatoes, cheese and peas; mix well.
Serve hot.

title: egg dish
directions: Boil eggs for 12 minutes. Set aside and let cool. Cut in half (not lengthwise), then slice a small amount off each bottom so they will set up on dish. After removing yolk, crumble bacon and nuts (both finely chopped) in small amounts into egg. Lightly season with salt and pepper. Then take egg yolks, curry, mayo and mustard and blend until smooth. Use pastry bag to squeeze mixture into egg halves. Sprinkle with more bacon and nut mixture over top and sprinkle with paprika. Number of servings: 12 to 18.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Beat good.
Sift together flour, salt and soda and add to mixture, mixing well.
Blend in oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in low oven.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Start cooker on high, then cook slow for 8 to 10 hours.
Stir once in awhile.
May leave lid off last 1/2 hour.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients with remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 425° oven for 8 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti (good if cooked in chicken broth) and drain. Layer spaghetti in buttered casserole dish (or use Pam), then add a layer of chicken, then onion-celery mixture that has been sauteed in margarine slowly until tender.
Top with mushroom soup (use less than 1/4 cup chicken broth to slightly thin soup).
Repeat layers. Top with sharp Cheddar cheese, grated (reduced fat).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: one cup cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and vanilla until it is a pancake batter consistency.
Melt butter in glass baking dish.
Pour fruit over melted butter.
Pour batter over fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake in a 375° to 400° oven until golden brown.
Inserted toothpick should come out clean.
Serve hot with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple. Fold in bread. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (cover dish).

title: spaghetti supreme
directions: In oblong baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches), sprinkle 2 cups of grated sharp cheese over hot boiled spaghetti. On top, place alternately the pork sausages (parboiled and then browned for 10 minutes) and the tomato slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour 1/2 cup of water over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift twice the flour, soda, ginger, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
Mix shortening, sugar, beaten eggs, cream and molasses until nice and smooth.
Add sifted mixture to it until doesn't stick to hands.
Roll and cut with large cutter.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown meat in oil. Add salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Push meat to one side in pan. Add onion and celery. Cook over low heat until soft.
Stir in bean sprouts, soup and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and top with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain yogurt in colander in refrigerator overnight.
Combine with salad dressing mix and mayonnaise in small bowl; mix well. Let stand 30 minutes.
Spread on bread slices.
Top each with cucumber slice and dill sprig.
Chill, covered, until serving time.

title: aunt mona's split pea soup with ham
directions: In a large pot, place ham bone and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: taco pie
directions: Place biscuits in a 10-inch pie pan and press together to form a crust like pie. Set aside. Saut in large skillet the turkey, onion and green pepper for 5 minutes. Add tomato paste and water. Sprinkle with taco seasoning. Simmer for 3 minutes. Layer half of the meat mixture on top of biscuit crust. Top with half of the cheese. Top with remaining meat mixture and cheese. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and bake in an unbaked deep dish pie shell. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Spread uncooked rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Arrange chicken over rice.
Mix the mushroom soup with the 2 cans water; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt sugar and margarine in skillet and caramelize, stirring constantly.
Add 2 1/2 cups milk and stir until mixture dissolves. Separate eggs and mix yolks, cornstarch and remaining milk together in bowl.
Remove from stove and cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: boiled crawfish
directions: Place a 30-quart pot filled with water one-quarter of the way full.
Place over high heat.
Add lemons, onions, rock salt, red pepper, mustard, crab boil mix, corn and potatoes; boil for 20 minutes.
The aroma is very strong.
Add crawfish; return to boil for 7 minutes.
Cover the pot; turn down the heat.
Allow to simmer 3 minutes.
Remove crawfish and liberally add table salt before peeling.

title: libby's famous pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pie shells. Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs lightly in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients in order given. Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: hershey's chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in small mixer bowl until blended.
Add cocoa alternating with milk, beating until smooth.
Gradually add and fold in nondairy whipped topping until well combined.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill until firm or freeze, if desired.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine everything, except meat, and heat together.
Add meat and continue simmering until the sauce has cooked down, approximately 30 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Combine in saucepan first 3 ingredients.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour batter into jelly roll pan or cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Boil noodles and drain.
Add mushrooms, green beans, tomato soup and sour cream.
In casserole dish, layer mixture and cheese.
End with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all (except topping) in a large bowl.
Form into a loaf.

title: beer cake
directions: Cream well the sugar and shortening.
Add all other ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Add beer and finish mixing. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Grease and flour pan.

title: barbecued ham on buns
directions: Cook onion in fat until clear.
Add all other ingredients except meat.
Thin to right consistency with tomato puree; put small pieces of shaved pressed ham in sauce shortly before serving time.
Serves 8.
Good also over cooked noodles.

title: magic coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; blend on low speed for 1 minute.
Pour mixture into a buttered (9-inch) pie plate.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until pie is set. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix melted oleo and stuffing mix.
Put half into bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken in layers on top of mix.
In a bowl, mix together soups and broth and pour over chicken.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: holiday easy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (yes including the frosting) in a large bowl and mix well. Generously oil or use nonstick cooking spray, a 9 x 13 cake pan or use a Bundt pan.
Bake until done or when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: spinach salad with apple and red onion
directions: Place spinach, apple and onion in a salad bowl. Place oil, vinegar, mustard and honey in a small plastic container and fit lid on container. Shake dressing to combine, 1 minute. Pour dressing over salad. Toss and season with salt and pepper to taste. Serves 4.

title: turkey taco salad(low cal)
directions: Brown turkey.
Add water and taco seasoning.
Boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine veggies (all but tomatoes).
Line platter with lettuce mixture.
Top with turkey mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Add tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla wedges.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables together and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in casserole dish, sprayed with Pam.
Crush 1 package of crackers and sprinkle on top.
Melt butter and drizzle over crumbs.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix lemon juice concentrate, condensed milk and whipped topping.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with meringue or whipped topping.
Chill pie until firm.

title: danish flavored cream cheesecake
directions: With electric mixer, beat together cheese, egg whites, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Turn into crumb crust.
Bake in 300° oven 1 hour.
Cool completely.
Top with whipped cream and fresh fruit to serve.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, eggs, onion, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli.
Place in a greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Melt margarine and mix with dressing mix; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh dew berry pie
directions: Line pan (12 x	9 x 2-inches) with 1 pie crust.
Spread fresh berries, sugar
and
margarine.
Top
with	other crust. Pour boiling water over	pie.
Bake
for
or
50 minutes or until juice is thick and crust is brown.

title: fried rice
directions: Brown hamburger and drain off excess grease.
Cut bacon into approximately 1-inch strips and fry until crispy done.
Scramble eggs.
Dice onions and mushrooms.
Drain water chestnuts.
Cook rice per instructions on box.
Combine all ingredients in large stock pot; mix well.
Serves approximately 5 to 7 people.

title: a pot of turnip greens
directions: Cook meat until it starts to get tender.
Add turnip greens. Add more water if needed.
Cook until greens are tender.
Corn meal dumplings and peeled Irish potatoes may be added about 30 minutes before greens are done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix everything with meat and cook in oven or electric roaster, tasting as it cooks and adding whatever is necessary.
Boil ten minutes; pack in jars and cook at 10 pounds pressure 25 minutes or cook 45 minutes; cool and freeze.

title: pea patties(what to do with leftover black-eyed peas)
directions: Mash peas with fork.
Add egg.
Add salt and pepper.
Add flour or corn meal.
Stir well.
Shape patties using 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Place patties in skillet with small amount of shortening or oil.
Brown, then turn over and brown other side.

title: frappe
directions: Mix ginger ale,
7-Up,	tartaric acid and partly thawed lime sherbet.
Mix well.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage (room temperature), cheese and Bisquick until well blended.
Roll into balls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: great grandmother shiffer's molasses cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and margarine; work like pie crumbs.
Set aside 1/2 cup crumbs for on top of cake.
Add molasses and hot water with baking soda dissolved in it.
Mix by hand into dry ingredients.
Pour into long pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix by hand, not with mixer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, soda, salt and baking powder. Beat eggs well in another bowl.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla and oil.
Then add dry ingredients.
Blend well; stir in zucchini. Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.

title: glazed graham crackers
directions: Break crackers in 1/4's and place on baking sheet.
Boil margarine and sugar 3 minutes and pour over crackers.
Sprinkle nuts over crackers.
Bake in oven for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Put all ingredients, except potatoes, in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Place potatoes in 12 x 15-inch casserole.
Break up and smooth evenly.
Pour cheese mixture over potatoes.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 16.
